/-- **T090 downstream bridge: slash by ╬▒ is `╬У_p(╬▒)`-invariant on ╬УтВБ(N)-cusp forms.**

For a ╬УтВБ(N)-slash-invariant function `f : тДН тЖТ тДВ` (e.g. a ╬УтВБ(N)-cusp form's
underlying function) and any `╬▒ тИИ GL (Fin 2) тДЪ`, the function `f тИг[k] ╬▒`
is invariant under the slash action of `╬У_p(╬▒) тКЖ SL(2, тДд)` (lifted to
GL(2, тДЭ) via `mapGL тДЭ`).

**Mathematical content.** For ╬│ тИИ ╬У_p(╬▒), `╬▒ ╬│ ╬▒тБ╗┬╣ тИИ ╬УтВБ(N)` (by
`Gamma_p_╬▒_conjBy_spec`), so `f тИг[k] (╬▒ ╬│ ╬▒тБ╗┬╣) = f`.  Rearranging via
slash composition: `(f тИг[k] ╬▒) тИг[k] ╬│ = f тИг[k] ╬▒`.

**Role for h_HeckeFD_swap.** This identifies `f тИг[k] ╬▒` as a function
invariant under `╬У_p(╬▒)` slash.  Combined with `[╬УтВБ(N) : ╬У_p(╬▒)]`-finite
index, the integral `тИл_{╬▒ тАв ╬У_p(╬▒)-FD} (f тИг[k] ╬▒)` is well-defined and
relates to `тИл_{╬УтВБ(N)-FD} f` via index multiplicity, giving the
fundamental-domain transport step underlying DS Thm 5.5.3.

This is the **first downstream consumer** of the ╬У_p(╬▒) / `conjBy`
infrastructure on the Hecke-FD bridge route. -/
lemma slash_╬▒_Gamma_p_╬▒_invariant (╬▒ : GL (Fin 2) тДЪ)
    (f : тДН тЖТ тДВ)
    (hf : тИА ╬┤ тИИ Gamma1 N,
      f тИг[k] ((mapGL тДЭ ╬┤ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) = f)
    {╬│ : SL(2, тДд)} (h╬│ : ╬│ тИИ Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒) :
    (f тИг[k] ((╬▒.map (Rat.castHom тДЭ) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ))) тИг[k]
      ((mapGL тДЭ ╬│ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) =
    f тИг[k] ((╬▒.map (Rat.castHom тДЭ) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) := by
  obtain тЯи╬┤, h╬┤_mem, h╬┤_eqтЯй := Gamma_p_╬▒_conj_mem_Gamma1 ╬▒ h╬│
  -- From h╬┤_eq: mapGL тДЭ ╬┤ = ╬▒' * mapGL тДЭ ╬│ * ╬▒'тБ╗┬╣ where ╬▒' = ╬▒.map (Rat.castHom тДЭ).
  -- So: ╬▒' * mapGL тДЭ ╬│ = mapGL тДЭ ╬┤ * ╬▒'.
  have h╬▒╬│ : (╬▒.map (Rat.castHom тДЭ) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
      (mapGL тДЭ ╬│ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      (mapGL тДЭ ╬┤ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) * (╬▒.map (Rat.castHom тДЭ) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := by
    rw [h╬┤_eq]; group
  -- Compute (f тИг ╬▒) тИг ╬│ via slash composition + ╬УтВБ(N)-invariance.
  rw [тЖР SlashAction.slash_mul, h╬▒╬│, SlashAction.slash_mul, hf ╬┤ h╬┤_mem]

