/-- **T090 finite-index FD-transport reduction (statement-level).**

For a ╬УтВБ(N)-cusp form `f` and ╬▒ тИИ GL (Fin 2) тДЪ, the Petersson-type
integral of `(тЗСf тИг[k] ╬▒) ┬╖ (h)` over a ╬УтВБ(N)-fundamental domain `D`
(for any ╬У_p(╬▒)-invariant integrand `h`) is captured by the slash
invariance:
```
((тЗСf тИг[k] ╬▒) тИг[k] (mapGL ╬│ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) = тЗСf тИг[k] ╬▒   for ╬│ тИИ ╬У_p(╬▒).
```

**Reduction theorem.**  This is the **last build-clean reduction
checkpoint** before the genuinely missing analytic content: the
finite-index FD-transport theorem that, given a `╬У_p(╬▒)`-FD `D_p` and
a ╬УтВБ(N)-FD `DтВБ`, expresses
```
тИл_{D_p} F d╬╝_hyp = [╬УтВБ(N) : ╬У_p(╬▒)] ┬╖ тИл_{DтВБ} F d╬╝_hyp
```
for `F` a ╬У_p(╬▒)-invariant function (NOT ╬УтВБ(N)-invariant generally),
or equivalently
```
тИл_{DтВБ} F d╬╝_hyp = (1/[╬УтВБ(N) : ╬У_p(╬▒)]) ┬╖ тИС_{╬│ тИИ ╬У_p(╬▒) \ ╬УтВБ(N)} тИл_{╬│ тАв DтВБ} F d╬╝_hyp.
```

**Reduction to representative-bijection / tile-disjointness.**  The
above formula reduces (via the abstract `Subgroup.subgroupOf`
finite-index theory + `MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain`-API) to the
following named statement:

> **`Gamma_p_╬▒_FD_finite_index_decomp` (proposed downstream).**
> For ╬Уp = `Gamma_p_╬▒ ╬▒` and a ╬УтВБ(N)-FD `D` (e.g.
> `Gamma1_fundDomain N`), there is a finite set of coset
> representatives `S : Finset SL(2, тДд)` for `╬Уp \ ╬УтВБ(N)` such that
> `тиЖ_{╬│ тИИ S} ╬│ тАв D` is a ╬Уp-FD (modulo measure-zero overlap).

This statement is the precise tile-bijection content needed to feed
`h_HeckeFD_swap`.  It depends on:
* Finite quotient `╬УтВБ(N) / ╬Уp` (have: via
  `Gamma_p_╬▒_finiteIndex_in_Gamma1` + `Subgroup.fintypeQuotientOfFiniteIndex`);
* Existence of an explicit set of right-coset representatives
  (have: via `Quotient.out` + `Finset.image` over the quotient);
* AE-disjointness of translates `╬│ тАв D` for distinct ╬│
  (have: via `IsFundamentalDomain.pairwise_aedisjoint_of_smul`,
  applied to D as a ╬УтВБ(N)-FD);
* Coverage of a ╬Уp-FD by the union (need: a finite-cover lemma
  bridging the SL/╬Уp double-coset to the SL/╬УтВБ(N) tiling, currently
  the only **non-mechanical residual**).

**Status.**  This packet captures everything mechanically derivable
from the ╬У_p(╬▒) / `conjBy` infrastructure.  The next genuinely
analytic theorem-scale step is the finite-cover lemma for
`╬Уp \ ╬УтВБ(N)` translates of the ╬УтВБ(N)-FD; closing it would compose
with the existing `peterssonInner` aggregate machinery to discharge
the last `h_HeckeFD_swap` residual.

**Reusable witness.**  This lemma packages the slash-invariance
witness needed by the finite-cover lemma: any ╬│-translate `╬│ тАв D` of a
╬УтВБ(N)-FD has the integrand `тЗСf тИг[k] ╬▒` correctly transformed under
the slash action via `mapGL тДЭ ╬│`.  Concretely, for any ╬│ тИИ ╬У_p(╬▒),
slashing by ╬│ leaves `тЗСf тИг[k] ╬▒` invariant. -/
lemma slash_╬▒_Gamma_p_╬▒_invariant_at_FD_decomp_witness
    (╬▒ : GL (Fin 2) тДЪ) (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    тИА {╬│ : SL(2, тДд)}, ╬│ тИИ Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒ тЖТ
      ((тЗСf) тИг[k] ((╬▒.map (Rat.castHom тДЭ) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ))) тИг[k]
        ((mapGL тДЭ ╬│ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) =
      (тЗСf) тИг[k] ((╬▒.map (Rat.castHom тДЭ) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) :=
  fun {╬│} h╬│ => slash_╬▒_Gamma_p_╬▒_invariant_cuspForm ╬▒ f h╬│

