/-- **T090 / T106 finite-index FD decomposition for `╬У_p(╬▒) тЙд ╬УтВБ(N)`
(conditional ambient form)**.

For any group `G_outer` containing both `╬УтВБ(N)` and `╬У_p(╬▒)` via a fixed
group hom `╧Ж : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* G_outer`, and for any `╬УтВБ(N).map ╧Ж`-fundamental
domain `D` on тДН, the union of `[╬УтВБ(N) : ╬У_p(╬▒)]`-many translates indexed
by `╬УтВБ(N).map ╧Ж тз╕ ((╬У_p(╬▒).map ╧Ж).subgroupOf (╬УтВБ(N).map ╧Ж))` is a
fundamental domain for the inner subgroup
`(╬У_p(╬▒).map ╧Ж).subgroupOf (╬УтВБ(N).map ╧Ж)`.

**Direct specialization** of the generic
`MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain.subgroup_iUnion_out_smul`
(`PeterssonLevelN.lean`:304) at the named subgroup pair `╬У_p(╬▒) тЙд ╬УтВБ(N)`
(lifted via `╧Ж`).  The `Countable` hypothesis on the right-coset space
is `[╬УтВБ(N) : ╬У_p(╬▒)]`-finite-index from `Gamma_p_╬▒_finiteIndex_in_Gamma1`
(transferred under `╧Ж` for injective `╧Ж`); supplied as an instance
argument so the caller wires it in at the ambient level.

**Conditional ambient тАФ kernel obstruction.**  This theorem is itself
unconditional, but its *useful* instantiations require the input
hypothesis `IsFundamentalDomain ((╬УтВБ(N)).map ╧Ж) D ╬╝_hyp` to actually be
satisfiable for the chosen `(G_outer, ╧Ж)`.  The latter depends on the
faithfulness of the `(╬УтВБ(N)).map ╧Ж`-action on тДН:

* **PSL ambient** (`G_outer := PSL(2, тДд)`, `╧Ж := QuotientGroup.mk' тЯи┬▒IтЯй`):
  the input FD is `isFundamentalDomain_Gamma1_PSL` (existing,
  `PeterssonLevelN.lean`:540).  Always available.  Limitation: cannot
  feed `Gamma_p_╬▒_GLPos_lift_FD_smul_conjAct` because the Hecke matrix
  `╬▒ : GL (Fin 2) тДЪ` does not embed into `PSL(2, тДд)` (its determinant
  varies).

* **GL(2, тДЭ)тБ║ ambient** (`G_outer := GL(2, тДЭ)тБ║`,
  `╧Ж := ModularGroup.coeHom`): the input FD `IsFundamentalDomain
  ((╬УтВБ(N)).map ModularGroup.coeHom) D ╬╝_hyp` is **provably FALSE** when
  `-I тИИ ╬УтВБ(N)`, i.e., when `N тИИ {1, 2}` тАФ the `┬▒I` kernel of the
  M├╢bius action collapses distinct group elements onto the same
  set-translate, breaking the pairwise `AEDisjoint` field of
  `IsFundamentalDomain`.  For `N тЙе 3` the action is faithful and the
  bridge is in principle provable, but no proof has been landed.

* **PGL(2, тДЭ)тБ║ / projective ambient** (proposed): use the projective
  quotient `GL(2, тДЭ)тБ║ / scalars` where the `┬▒I` kernel is moded out and
  `╬▒` retains a well-defined image.  This is the natural replacement
  API for general `N`, and is the next bridge step before downstream
  `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge` consumption.

**Use site (DS Prop. 5.5.2(b), conditional).**  Combined with the
FD-shift adapter `Gamma_p_╬▒_GLPos_lift_FD_smul_conjAct` (at the
projective-equivalent ambient), this would provide the per-╬▒
tile-decomposition needed for the `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge` proof:
starting from a ╬УтВБ(N)-FD `D`, decompose into a ╬У_p(╬▒)-FD via the
finite-index coset-tile union, then ╬▒-shift the result to obtain the
`╬▒ ┬╖ ╬У_p(╬▒) ┬╖ ╬▒тБ╗┬╣`-FD whose Petersson integral hosts the per-╬▒
slash-adjoint shift.  The wiring is blocked on landing the projective
ambient (or restricting to `N тЙе 3` if the project caller commits to
that hypothesis). -/
theorem Gamma_p_╬▒_FD_finite_index_decomp
    {G_outer : Type*} [Group G_outer] [MulAction G_outer тДН]
    [MeasurableConstSMul G_outer тДН] [SMulInvariantMeasure G_outer тДН ╬╝_hyp]
    (╬▒ : GL (Fin 2) тДЪ) (╧Ж : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* G_outer) {D : Set тДН}
    (hD : IsFundamentalDomain ((Gamma1 N).map ╧Ж) D ╬╝_hyp)
    [Countable
      (((Gamma1 N).map ╧Ж) тз╕
        (((Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒).map ╧Ж).subgroupOf ((Gamma1 N).map ╧Ж)))] :
    IsFundamentalDomain
      (((Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒).map ╧Ж).subgroupOf ((Gamma1 N).map ╧Ж))
      (тЛГ q : ((Gamma1 N).map ╧Ж) тз╕
              (((Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒).map ╧Ж).subgroupOf ((Gamma1 N).map ╧Ж)),
        ((q.out : ((Gamma1 N).map ╧Ж)) : G_outer)тБ╗┬╣ тАв D)
      ╬╝_hyp :=
  hD.subgroup_iUnion_out_smul _

