/-- **Phase E1 тАФ finite-index instance for the projective image of `╬У_p(╬▒)`
inside the projective image of `╬УтВБ(N)`.**

The subgroup `(╬У_p(╬▒)).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R` has finite index in
`(╬УтВБ(N)).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R`, lifting the integer-side finite-index witness
`Gamma_p_╬▒_finiteIndex` along the (non-injective) hom `SL2Z_to_PSL2R`.

**Key lemma**: `Subgroup.relIndex_map_map` rewrites
`((map f H).subgroupOf (map f K)).index = (map f H).relIndex (map f K)
  = (H тКФ f.ker).relIndex (K тКФ f.ker)`.
Since `╬У_p(╬▒)` already has finite index in `SL(2, тДд)` (`Gamma_p_╬▒_finiteIndex`),
so does the larger group `╬У_p(╬▒) тКФ ker SL2Z_to_PSL2R`
(`Subgroup.finiteIndex_of_le`), and consequently its `subgroupOf` has finite
index (`Subgroup.instFiniteIndex_subgroupOf`).

**Use site**: provides the `[Countable тАж]` instance hypothesis required by
`Gamma_p_╬▒_PSL_R_FD_finite_index_decomp` automatically, removing the need
for downstream callers to thread that instance manually. -/
instance Gamma_p_╬▒_image_PSL_R_finiteIndex_in_Gamma1_image
    (╬▒ : GL (Fin 2) тДЪ) :
    (((Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).subgroupOf
      ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R)).FiniteIndex := by
  haveI : (Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒).FiniteIndex := Gamma_p_╬▒_finiteIndex ╬▒
  haveI : (Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒ тКФ SL2Z_to_PSL2R.ker).FiniteIndex :=
    Subgroup.finiteIndex_of_le le_sup_left
  refine тЯи?_тЯй
  show ((Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).relIndex
        ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R) тЙа 0
  rw [Subgroup.relIndex_map_map]
  exact (Subgroup.instFiniteIndex_subgroupOf
    (Gamma1 N тКФ SL2Z_to_PSL2R.ker)
    (H := Gamma_p_╬▒ (N := N) ╬▒ тКФ SL2Z_to_PSL2R.ker)).index_ne_zero

