/-- **T126 coset-reindex helper (cusp-form version)**: for a `╬УтВБ(N)`-cusp
form `g` and `╬│ тИИ ╬УтВА(N)`, slashing by `(╧Г q).outтБ╗┬╣` where
`╧Г = Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0 ╬│` equals slashing by `q.outтБ╗┬╣` after applying
the diamond operator `тЯиGamma0MapUnits ╬│тЯй`.

Captures the core "╬УтВА(N)-coset-reindex absorbs into diamond shift" identity:
under the `q тЖж q┬╖╬│тБ╗┬╣` reindex of `SL(2, тДд) тз╕ ╬УтВБ(N)`, the slashed cusp form
`g тИг[k] (╧Г q).outтБ╗┬╣` collapses to `(тЯиGamma0MapUnits ╬│тЯй g) тИг[k] q.outтБ╗┬╣`.

**Role in T205 closure.**  This is the precise sub-lemma missing for the
`q тЖж q┬╖╬│тВАтБ╗┬╣` reindex in `petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core`: applied at
╬│ = `adjointGamma0Rep` (so `Gamma0MapUnits ╬│ = uтБ╗┬╣`), we get the identity
`g тИг (╧Г q).outтБ╗┬╣ = (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯй g) тИг q.outтБ╗┬╣` for ╬УтВБ(N)-cusp forms on the
"outer" `g` slot of `peterssonInner k fd (┬╖ тИг qтБ╗┬╣) (g тИг qтБ╗┬╣)`.

**Proof.**  By definition of `Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0`, `(╧Г q) = тЯжq.out┬╖╬│тБ╗┬╣тЯз`
in `SL(2, тДд) тз╕ ╬УтВБ(N)`.  Extract `╬╖тВА тИИ ╬УтВБ(N)` with
`(╧Г q).out = q.out ┬╖ ╬│тБ╗┬╣ ┬╖ ╬╖тВАтБ╗┬╣`; then `(╧Г q).outтБ╗┬╣ = ╬╖тВА ┬╖ ╬│ ┬╖ q.outтБ╗┬╣`.
Using `slash_Gamma1_eq` to absorb `╬╖тВА` and `diamondOpCusp_eq` to identify
`g тИг ╬│` with `тЯиGamma0MapUnits ╬│тЯй g`, the identity follows. -/
theorem slash_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq_diamond_slash_out_inv
    (╬│ : тЖе(Gamma0 N)) (g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k)
    (q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N) :
    тЗСg тИг[k] ((Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0 (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) ╬│.property q).out :
      SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ =
    тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) g) тИг[k]
      (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ := by
  -- Step 1: extract ╬╖тВА тИИ ╬УтВБ(N) with (╧Г q).out = q.out ┬╖ ╬│тБ╗┬╣ ┬╖ ╬╖тВАтБ╗┬╣.
  set ╧Г := Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0 (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) ╬│.property
  have h_coset_eq : (╧Г q) = тЯжq.out * (╬│ : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣тЯз := by
    conv_lhs => rw [show q = тЯжq.outтЯз from q.out_eq.symm]
    rfl
  have h_out_eq_mk : тЯж(╧Г q).outтЯз = (тЯжq.out * (╬│ : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣тЯз :
      SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N) := by
    rw [тЖР h_coset_eq, (╧Г q).out_eq]
  have h_mem : ((╧Г q).out)тБ╗┬╣ * (q.out * (╬│ : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣) тИИ Gamma1 N := by
    have h_left_rel := Quotient.exact h_out_eq_mk
    change (QuotientGroup.leftRel _).r _ _ at h_left_rel
    rwa [QuotientGroup.leftRel_apply] at h_left_rel
  set ╬╖тВА := ((╧Г q).out)тБ╗┬╣ * (q.out * (╬│ : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
  -- Step 2: `(╧Г q).out = q.out ┬╖ ╬│тБ╗┬╣ ┬╖ ╬╖тВАтБ╗┬╣`, so `(╧Г q).outтБ╗┬╣ = ╬╖тВА ┬╖ ╬│ ┬╖ q.outтБ╗┬╣`.
  have h_inv_eq : ((╧Г q).out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ =
      ╬╖тВА * (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) * ((q.out : SL(2, тДд)))тБ╗┬╣ := by
    show ((╧Г q).out)тБ╗┬╣ = ╬╖тВА * (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) * (q.out)тБ╗┬╣
    show ((╧Г q).out)тБ╗┬╣ = (((╧Г q).out)тБ╗┬╣ * (q.out * (╬│ : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)) *
        (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) * (q.out)тБ╗┬╣
    group
  rw [h_inv_eq, SlashAction.slash_mul, SlashAction.slash_mul]
  -- Step 3: slash by ╬╖тВА тИИ ╬УтВБ(N) is identity on cusp form g.
  rw [show тЗСg тИг[k] ╬╖тВА = тЗСg from
    SlashInvariantFormClass.slash_action_eq g _
      (Subgroup.mem_map.mpr тЯи╬╖тВА, h_mem, rflтЯй)]
  -- Step 4: slash by ╬│ тИИ ╬УтВА(N) is diamond operator on cusp form g.
  rw [show тЗСg тИг[k] (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) =
    тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) g) from by
    show тЗСg тИг[k] (mapGL тДЭ (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) = _
    show тЗСg тИг[k] (mapGL тДЭ (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      тЗС(diamondOpCusp k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) g)
    rw [diamondOpCusp_eq k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) ╬│ rfl]
    rfl]

open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T128 Hecke-diamond whole-cusp-form coset-reindex helper**: for a
`╬УтВБ(N)`-cusp form `g` and `╬│ тИИ ╬УтВА(N)`, slashing the full `T_p`-image
`heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g` by `(╧Г q).outтБ╗┬╣` (where
`╧Г = Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0 ╬│`) equals slashing
`heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN (тЯиGamma0MapUnits ╬│тЯй g)` by `q.outтБ╗┬╣`.

Composes T126 (`slash_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq_diamond_slash_out_inv`)
with `heckeT_p_comm_diamondOp` (the `ModularForm`-level Hecke/diamond
commutation) to push the diamond twist inside `T_p_cusp` at function level.

**Role in T205 closure.** The `q тЖж q┬╖╬│тВАтБ╗┬╣` reindex on the
`heckeT_p_cusp g` side is absorbed into a single diamond twist of `g`,
simultaneously covering BOTH residual non-invariant slash terms of the
naive double-coset decomposition тАФ the upper-ut sum
`heckeT_p_ut k p hp.pos тЗСg` and the `M_тИЮ` piece
`тЗСg тИг[k] M_тИЮ` тАФ since they are the two components of the single quantity
`heckeT_p_cusp g тИг[k] (╧Г q).outтБ╗┬╣`.  This sidesteps the per-`b`
permutation/conjugation route (which fails because the naive matrix
conjugate `T_p_upper(b) ┬╖ ╬│тВА ┬╖ T_p_upper(b)тБ╗┬╣` has non-integer entries
in general). -/
theorem slash_heckeT_p_cusp_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (╬│ : тЖе(Gamma0 N)) (g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k)
    (q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N) :
    тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) тИг[k]
      ((Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0 (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) ╬│.property q).out :
        SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ =
    тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN
        (diamondOp_cusp k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) g)) тИг[k]
      (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ := by
  -- Step 1: apply T126 helper to `heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g`.
  rw [slash_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq_diamond_slash_out_inv ╬│
      (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) q]
  set d := Gamma0MapUnits ╬│ with hd_def
  -- Goal: тЗС(тЯиdтЯй_cusp (T_p_cusp g)) тИг q.outтБ╗┬╣ = тЗС(T_p_cusp (тЯиdтЯй_cusp g)) тИг q.outтБ╗┬╣
  -- Reduce to equality of the underlying functions.
  suffices h_eq : (тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k d (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) :
      UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) =
      тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN (diamondOp_cusp k d g)) by
    rw [h_eq]
  -- Step 2: diamondOp_cusp at function level is slash by ╬│.
  have h_diamond_cusp_coe : тИА (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k),
      (тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k d f) : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) =
      (тЗСf : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) тИг[k]
        (mapGL тДЭ (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := fun f => by
    show (тЗС(diamondOpCusp k d f) : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) = _
    rw [diamondOpCusp_eq k d ╬│ rfl]
    rfl
  -- Step 3: diamondOp (ModularForm) at function level is slash by ╬│.
  have h_diamond_mf_coe : тИА (F : ModularForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k),
      (тЗС(diamondOp k d F) : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) =
      (тЗСF : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) тИг[k]
        (mapGL тДЭ (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := fun F => by
    rw [diamondOp_eq_diamondOpAux k d ╬│ rfl]
    rfl
  -- Step 4: heckeT_p commutes with diamondOp (ModularForm level), applied to g.toModularForm'.
  have h_comm_app : diamondOp k d (heckeT_p k p hp hpN g.toModularForm') =
      heckeT_p k p hp hpN (diamondOp k d g.toModularForm') :=
    LinearMap.congr_fun
      (heckeT_p_comm_diamondOp (N := N) k p hp hpN d) g.toModularForm'
  -- Step 5: heckeT_p's value (as a function) depends only on тЗСF (via heckeT_p_fun_eq_coset_sum).
  have h_heckeT_p_congr : тИА (FтВБ FтВВ : ModularForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k),
      (тЗСFтВБ : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) = тЗСFтВВ тЖТ
      (тЗС(heckeT_p k p hp hpN FтВБ) : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) =
      тЗС(heckeT_p k p hp hpN FтВВ) := fun FтВБ FтВВ hF => by
    show heckeT_p_fun k p hp hpN FтВБ = heckeT_p_fun k p hp hpN FтВВ
    rw [heckeT_p_fun_eq_coset_sum k hp hpN FтВБ,
      heckeT_p_fun_eq_coset_sum k hp hpN FтВВ, hF]
  -- Step 6: chain the equalities.
  calc (тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k d (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) :
        UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ)
      = (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) тИг[k]
          (mapGL тДЭ (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := h_diamond_cusp_coe _
    _ = (тЗС(heckeT_p k p hp hpN g.toModularForm') : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) тИг[k]
          (mapGL тДЭ (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := rfl
    _ = тЗС(diamondOp k d (heckeT_p k p hp hpN g.toModularForm')) :=
          (h_diamond_mf_coe _).symm
    _ = тЗС(heckeT_p k p hp hpN (diamondOp k d g.toModularForm')) := by
          rw [h_comm_app]
    _ = тЗС(heckeT_p k p hp hpN (diamondOp_cusp k d g).toModularForm') := by
          apply h_heckeT_p_congr
          rw [h_diamond_mf_coe, show (тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k d g).toModularForm' :
            UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ) = тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k d g) from rfl,
            h_diamond_cusp_coe]
          rfl
    _ = тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN (diamondOp_cusp k d g)) := rfl

open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T128 petN-level q-reindex consumer**: applying the T128 pointwise
identity across the full `тИС_q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ ╬УтВБ(N)` sum (via `Equiv.sum_comp`
on `╧Г = Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0 ╬│`, combined with T128 on the first
`peterssonInner` slot and T126 on the second) collapses to a `petN`
identity:
`petN (T_p f) g = petN (T_p (тЯиGamma0MapUnits ╬│тЯй f)) (тЯиGamma0MapUnits ╬│тЯй g)`
for any `╬│ тИИ ╬УтВА(N)` and ╬УтВБ(N)-cusp forms `f, g`.

This consumer transforms a concrete `petN (T_p f) g` expression into
another `petN` expression whose arguments carry a symmetric diamond
twist тАФ a tangible q-sum/petN reshape, not a pointwise restatement.

**Role in T205.** Specialized at `╬│ = adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN` (with
`Gamma0MapUnits ╬│ = uтБ╗┬╣` via `adjointGamma0Rep_units`), it gives
`petN (T_p f) g = petN (T_p (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯй f)) (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯй g)`, which is the exact
╧Г-reindex form that appears in the T205 residual after the `╬│тВА`-slash
simplification path.

**Proof route.** `petN` unfolds to a `тИС_q` of `peterssonInner` on
slashed cusp forms. Reindexing `q тЖж ╧Г q` via `Equiv.sum_comp ╧Г` shifts
each summand to use `(╧Г q).outтБ╗┬╣`. T128 absorbs the ╧Г-shift on the
first `T_p_cusp f` slot and T126 absorbs it on the second `g` slot,
both yielding `q.outтБ╗┬╣` slashes on diamond-twisted cusp forms. -/
theorem petN_heckeT_p_Gamma1QuotEquiv_reindex
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (╬│ : тЖе(Gamma0 N)) (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN
              (diamondOp_cusp k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) f))
           (diamondOp_cusp k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) g) := by
  -- Unfold `petN` on both sides to `тИС_q peterssonInner ...` form.
  show тИС q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N,
        peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
          (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
          (тЗСg тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣) =
      тИС q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N,
        peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
          (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN
             (diamondOp_cusp k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) f)) тИг[k]
            (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
          (тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k (Gamma0MapUnits ╬│) g) тИг[k]
            (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
  -- Reindex the LHS sum by q тЖж ╧Г q via `Equiv.sum_comp ╧Г`.
  rw [тЖР Equiv.sum_comp (Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0 (╬│ : SL(2, тДд)) ╬│.property)
    (fun q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N =>
      peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
        (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
        (тЗСg тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣))]
  -- Apply T128 (first slot) and T126 (second slot) pointwise.
  refine Finset.sum_congr rfl fun q _ => ?_
  rw [slash_heckeT_p_cusp_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq p hp hpN ╬│ f q,
    slash_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq_diamond_slash_out_inv ╬│ g q]

/-- **T128 specialization at `adjointGamma0Rep`**: the T128-based
q-reindex consumer applied at `╬│ = adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN`, yielding
a symmetric `тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯй`-twist form:
`petN (T_p f) g = petN (T_p (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯй f)) (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯй g)`.

This is the concrete T205 q-sum/petN residual consumer that uses the
T128 helper at the adjoint ╬УтВА(N) representative: the bottom-right
entry `Gamma0MapUnits (adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN) = uтБ╗┬╣` comes from the
`adjointGamma0Rep_units` identification. -/
private theorem petN_heckeT_p_adjointGamma0Rep_reindex
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN
              (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ f))
           (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ g) := by
  have h := petN_heckeT_p_Gamma1QuotEquiv_reindex p hp hpN
    (adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN) f g
  rw [adjointGamma0Rep_units p N hpN] at h
  exact h

open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T128 petN-level RHS q-reindex consumer**: analog of
`petN_heckeT_p_adjointGamma0Rep_reindex` for `T_p` on the second slot.
Applying T126 (`slash_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq_diamond_slash_out_inv`) on
slot 1 and T128 (`slash_heckeT_p_cusp_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq`) on slot 2
across the full `тИС_q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ ╬УтВБ(N)` sum, specialized at
`╬│ = adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN` (so `Gamma0MapUnits ╬│ = uтБ╗┬╣`), yields
`petN f (T_p g) = petN (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯй f) (T_p (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯй g))`.

Together with `petN_heckeT_p_adjointGamma0Rep_reindex`, this is the other half
of the outer two-stage q-reindex used by `petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core`
before any per-q commit. -/
private theorem petN_f_heckeT_p_adjointGamma0Rep_reindex
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN f (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) =
      petN (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ f)
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN
          (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ g)) := by
  show тИС q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N,
        peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
          (тЗСf тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
          (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣) =
      тИС q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N,
        peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
          (тЗС(diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ f) тИг[k]
            (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
          (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN
              (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ g)) тИг[k]
            (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
  rw [тЖР Equiv.sum_comp (Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0
    ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд))
    (adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN).property)
    (fun q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N =>
      peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
        (тЗСf тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)
        (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣))]
  refine Finset.sum_congr rfl fun q _ => ?_
  rw [slash_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq_diamond_slash_out_inv
      (adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN) f q,
    slash_heckeT_p_cusp_Gamma1QuotEquiv_out_inv_eq p hp hpN
      (adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN) g q,
    adjointGamma0Rep_units p N hpN]

/-- **Adjugate `T_p_upper(0) тЖТ T_p_lower` identity** (GLтВВ(тДЭ)-level).

Both `peterssonAdj (glMap T_p_upper(0))` and `glMap T_p_lower` have underlying
matrix `[[p, 0], [0, 1]]` over тДЭ.  This is the reverse direction of
`peterssonAdj_glMap_T_p_lower_eq_glMap_T_p_upper_zero`; both are needed for
the M_тИЮ-adjoint alignment. -/
private lemma peterssonAdj_glMap_T_p_upper_zero_eq_glMap_T_p_lower
    (p : тДХ) (hp : 0 < p) :
    peterssonAdj (glMap (T_p_upper p hp 0) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      (glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := by
  apply Units.ext
  ext i j
  have h_L := peterssonAdj_glMap_T_p_upper p hp 0
  simp only [Nat.cast_zero, neg_zero] at h_L
  have h_R : ((glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) :
      Matrix (Fin 2) (Fin 2) тДЭ) = !![(p : тДЭ), 0; 0, (1 : тДЭ)] := by
    ext i' j'; fin_cases i' <;> fin_cases j' <;> simp [glMap, T_p_lower]
  show (peterssonAdj (glMap (T_p_upper p hp 0) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) :
      Matrix _ _ тДЭ) i j =
    ((glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) : Matrix _ _ тДЭ) i j
  rw [h_L, h_R]

/-- **M_тИЮ adjoint b-collapse alignment helper**: per-summand slash-adjoint
identity aligning the `none` branch of the Option `(Fin p)` family with the
same constant RHS target `(тЗСg тИг glMap T_p_upper(0)) тИг mapGL ╬│тВА` as the
`some b` branch.

Matches the form of `slash_peterssonAdj_T_p_upper_eq_slash_T_p_upper_zero_slash_gamma0`
(the `some b` collapse via `slash_peterssonAdj_T_p_upper_adjointGamma0Rep_inv_eq_T_p_upper_zero`
at any `b тИИ Fin p`) but for the `none = M_тИЮ` branch.

**Proof composition.**
* Use `glMap_T_p_upper_inv_mul_M_infty_eq_mapGL_Gamma1` at `b = 0` to derive
  `glMap M_тИЮ = glMap T_p_upper(0) ┬╖ mapGL (M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0)`.
* Take adjoint; use `peterssonAdj_mul` + `peterssonAdj_mapGL_SL_eq_inv` +
  `peterssonAdj_glMap_T_p_upper_zero_eq_glMap_T_p_lower` to simplify
  `peterssonAdj (glMap M_тИЮ)` to
  `mapGL (M_infty_Gamma1_factor 0)тБ╗┬╣ ┬╖ glMap T_p_lower`.
* `M_infty_Gamma1_factor_mem_Gamma1` provides ╬УтВБ(N) membership; its inverse
  is in ╬УтВБ(N), so `тЗСg тИг mapGL factorтБ╗┬╣ = тЗСg` by ╬УтВБ(N)-invariance.
* `slash_T_p_lower_eq_T_p_upper_zero_slash_gamma0` converts
  `тЗСg тИг glMap T_p_lower` to the common RHS target. -/
private lemma slash_peterssonAdj_glMap_M_infty_eq_slash_T_p_upper_zero_slash_gamma0
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    тЗСg тИг[k] peterssonAdj (glMap (M_infty N p hp.pos hpN) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      (тЗСg тИг[k] (glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos 0) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) тИг[k]
        ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
          ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд))) := by
  -- Step 1: glMap M_тИЮ = glMap T_p_upper(0) * mapGL (M_infty_Gamma1_factor 0).
  have h_inv_prod :=
    glMap_T_p_upper_inv_mul_M_infty_eq_mapGL_Gamma1 N p hp.pos hpN 0
  have h_M_infty_eq : (glMap (M_infty N p hp.pos hpN) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      (glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos 0) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
        ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _) (M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0)) := by
    rw [тЖР h_inv_prod, mul_inv_cancel_left]
  -- Step 2: take the adjoint of the factored form.
  rw [h_M_infty_eq, peterssonAdj_mul, peterssonAdj_mapGL_SL_eq_inv,
    peterssonAdj_glMap_T_p_upper_zero_eq_glMap_T_p_lower]
  -- Step 3: rewrite `(mapGL тДЭ factor)тБ╗┬╣` as `mapGL тДЭ factorтБ╗┬╣`.
  rw [тЖР map_inv, SlashAction.slash_mul]
  -- Step 4: `factorтБ╗┬╣ тИИ ╬УтВБ(N)` acts trivially on `g`.
  have hfactor_mem := M_infty_Gamma1_factor_mem_Gamma1 N p hpN 0
  have hfactor_inv_mem : (M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0)тБ╗┬╣ тИИ Gamma1 N :=
    inv_mem hfactor_mem
  have h_g_slash : тЗСg тИг[k] ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
        (M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0)тБ╗┬╣) = тЗСg :=
    SlashInvariantFormClass.slash_action_eq g _
      тЯи(M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0)тБ╗┬╣, hfactor_inv_mem, rflтЯй
  rw [h_g_slash]
  -- Step 5: T_p_lower тЖТ T_p_upper(0) + ╬│тВА bridge.
  exact slash_T_p_lower_eq_T_p_upper_zero_slash_gamma0 p hp hpN g

/-- **T024 uniform peterssonAdj M_тИЮ slash on cusp form**: for cusp form `g`,
`g тИг peterssonAdj M_тИЮ = g тИг T_p_lower`. Combines
`slash_peterssonAdj_glMap_M_infty_eq_slash_T_p_upper_zero_slash_gamma0`
(which gives `(g тИг T_p_upper(0)) тИг ╬│тВА`) with
`slash_T_p_lower_eq_T_p_upper_zero_slash_gamma0.symm` (which converts back to
`g тИг T_p_lower`).

This is the **M_тИЮ branch** of the uniform `g тИг peterssonAdj ╬▒ = g тИг T_p_lower`
identity for `╬▒ тИИ T_p reps`, key to the petN T_p-side reduction
`petN(T_p f, g) = peterssonInner k (T_p ┬╖ ╬УтВБ_FD) f (g тИг T_p_lower)`. -/
private lemma slash_peterssonAdj_glMap_M_infty_eq_slash_T_p_lower
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    тЗСg тИг[k] peterssonAdj (glMap (M_infty N p hp.pos hpN) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      тЗСg тИг[k] (glMap (T_p_lower p hp.pos) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := by
  rw [slash_peterssonAdj_glMap_M_infty_eq_slash_T_p_upper_zero_slash_gamma0
    p hp hpN g]
  exact (slash_T_p_lower_eq_T_p_upper_zero_slash_gamma0 p hp hpN g).symm

/-- **T024 uniform peterssonAdj T_p_upper(b) slash on cusp form**: for cusp
form `g` and any `b : тДХ`, `g тИг peterssonAdj T_p_upper(b) = g тИг T_p_lower`.
Composes:
* `peterssonAdj_T_p_upper_eq_shift_mul_lower`: `peterssonAdj T_p_upper(b)
  = mapGL (shiftSL_loc(-b)) ┬╖ glMap T_p_lower`;
* `SlashAction.slash_mul`: distributes the slash;
* `SlashInvariantFormClass.slash_action_eq` with
  `shiftSL_loc_mem_Gamma1`: `g тИг shiftSL_loc(-b) = g`.

This is the **T_p_upper(b) branch** of the uniform
`g тИг peterssonAdj ╬▒ = g тИг T_p_lower` identity for `╬▒ тИИ T_p reps`. -/
private lemma slash_peterssonAdj_glMap_T_p_upper_eq_slash_T_p_lower
    (p : тДХ) (hp : 0 < p) (b : тДХ)
    (g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    тЗСg тИг[k] peterssonAdj (glMap (T_p_upper p hp b) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      тЗСg тИг[k] (glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := by
  rw [peterssonAdj_T_p_upper_eq_shift_mul_lower p hp b, SlashAction.slash_mul,
    show (тЗСg тИг[k] ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
      (shiftSL_loc (-(b : тДд))) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) = тЗСg from
        SlashInvariantFormClass.slash_action_eq g _
          тЯиshiftSL_loc (-(b : тДд)), shiftSL_loc_mem_Gamma1 _, rflтЯй]

/-! ### T128 DS-standard `╬┤_b` representative-system helpers

The `╬┤_b тИИ ╬УтВБ(N)` matrix realizing `╬│тВА ┬╖ T_p_upper(b) = T_p_lower ┬╖ ╬┤_b` for
`╬│тВА = adjointGamma0Rep`.  These are the candidates for a complete
representative system of `H_L \ ╬УтВБ(N)` where
`H_L := ╬УтВБ(N) тИй T_p_lowerтБ╗┬╣ ┬╖ ╬УтВБ(N) ┬╖ T_p_lower`. -/

/-- **T128 lower-branch `╬┤_b` ╬УтВБ(N)-factor.**  The SL(2, тДд) matrix
`!![1, b тИТ gcdB(p,N); N, Nb + p ┬╖ gcdA(p,N)]`.  Realizes
`╬│тВА ┬╖ T_p_upper(b) = T_p_lower ┬╖ mapGL ╬┤_b` as GL(2, тДЭ) elements, where
`╬│тВА = adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN`. -/
private noncomputable def gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor
    (N p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N) (b : тДХ) : SL(2, тДд) :=
  тЯи!![1, (b : тДд) - Int.gcdB p N;
      (N : тДд), (N : тДд) * b + (p : тДд) * Int.gcdA p N],
    by
      have hbez := Int.gcd_eq_gcd_ab (p : тДд) (N : тДд)
      rw [show (Int.gcd (тЖСp) (тЖСN) : тДд) = 1 from by exact_mod_cast hpN] at hbez
      rw [Matrix.det_fin_two_of]; linarithтЯй

/-- **T128: `gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor` lies in `╬УтВБ(N)`.** -/
private theorem gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor_mem_Gamma1
    (N p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N) (b : тДХ) :
    gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN b тИИ Gamma1 N := by
  rw [Gamma1_mem]
  have hbez := Int.gcd_eq_gcd_ab (p : тДд) (N : тДд)
  rw [show (Int.gcd (тЖСp) (тЖСN) : тДд) = 1 from by exact_mod_cast hpN] at hbez
  have hN_zmod : ((N : тДХ) : ZMod N) = 0 := ZMod.natCast_self N
  have hpgcdA_mod : ((p : ZMod N) : ZMod N) * ((Int.gcdA p N : тДд) : ZMod N) = 1 := by
    have := congr_arg ((тЖС) : тДд тЖТ ZMod N) hbez.symm
    push_cast at this
    -- `this` is тЖСp * тЖС(gcdA p N) + тЖСN * тЖС(gcdB p N) = 1 in ZMod N
    rw [hN_zmod, zero_mul, add_zero] at this
    exact this
  refine тЯи?_, ?_, ?_тЯй
  ┬╖ change ((1 : тДд) : ZMod N) = 1
    push_cast; rfl
  ┬╖ change (((N : тДд) * b + (p : тДд) * Int.gcdA p N : тДд) : ZMod N) = 1
    push_cast
    rw [hN_zmod]
    simp only [zero_mul, zero_add]
    exact hpgcdA_mod
  ┬╖ change (((N : тДд) : тДд) : ZMod N) = 0
    push_cast
    exact ZMod.natCast_self N

/-- **T128: The DS-standard matrix identity**: for `╬│тВА = adjointGamma0Rep
p N hpN` and any `b : тДХ`, `╬│тВА ┬╖ T_p_upper(b) = T_p_lower ┬╖ mapGL ╬┤_b`
in `GL(2, тДЭ)`, where `╬┤_b = gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN b`. -/
private theorem mapGL_gamma0_mul_T_p_upper_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_delta
    (N p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hp : 0 < p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N) (b : тДХ) :
    ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
      (glMap (T_p_upper p hp b) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
    (glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
      ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        (gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN b) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := by
  -- Direct matrix comparison.
  apply Units.ext
  ext i j
  have hbez : (Int.gcdA p N : тДд) * p + (Int.gcdB p N : тДд) * N = 1 := by
    have h := Int.gcd_eq_gcd_ab (p : тДд) (N : тДд)
    rw [show (Int.gcd (тЖСp) (тЖСN) : тДд) = 1 from by exact_mod_cast hpN] at h
    linarith
  -- Unfold ╬│тВА = adjointGamma0Rep = !![p, -gcdB; N, gcdA] (over тДЭ).
  have h_gamma0_mat : (((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
      ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) :
      Matrix (Fin 2) (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      !![(p : тДЭ), -((Int.gcdB p N : тДд) : тДЭ); (N : тДЭ), ((Int.gcdA p N : тДд) : тДЭ)] := by
    ext i' j'
    fin_cases i' <;> fin_cases j' <;>
      simp [adjointGamma0Rep, mapGL_coe_matrix, algebraMap_int_eq, Matrix.of_apply]
  have h_Tu_mat : ((glMap (T_p_upper p hp b) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) :
      Matrix (Fin 2) (Fin 2) тДЭ) = !![(1 : тДЭ), (b : тДЭ); 0, (p : тДЭ)] := by
    ext i' j'; fin_cases i' <;> fin_cases j' <;>
      simp [glMap, T_p_upper, Matrix.GeneralLinearGroup.mkOfDetNeZero,
        Matrix.GeneralLinearGroup.map, Matrix.of_apply]
  have h_Tl_mat : ((glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) :
      Matrix (Fin 2) (Fin 2) тДЭ) = !![(p : тДЭ), 0; 0, 1] := by
    ext i' j'; fin_cases i' <;> fin_cases j' <;>
      simp [glMap, T_p_lower, Matrix.GeneralLinearGroup.mkOfDetNeZero,
        Matrix.GeneralLinearGroup.map, Matrix.of_apply]
  have h_delta_mat : (((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
      (gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN b) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) :
      Matrix (Fin 2) (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      !![(1 : тДЭ), ((b : тДЭ) - ((Int.gcdB p N : тДд) : тДЭ));
         (N : тДЭ), ((N : тДЭ) * b + (p : тДЭ) * ((Int.gcdA p N : тДд) : тДЭ))] := by
    ext i' j'; fin_cases i' <;> fin_cases j' <;>
      simp [mapGL_coe_matrix, gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor, algebraMap_int_eq,
        Matrix.of_apply]
  show ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд)) *
      (glMap (T_p_upper p hp b) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ).val i j =
    ((glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
      ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        (gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN b) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)).val i j
  rw [Units.val_mul, Units.val_mul, h_gamma0_mat, h_Tu_mat, h_Tl_mat, h_delta_mat]
  fin_cases i <;> fin_cases j <;>
    simp [Matrix.mul_apply, Fin.sum_univ_two, Matrix.of_apply] <;> ring

/-- **T128 `M_тИЮ` branch of the DS p+1 coset family factorization**:
the `M_тИЮ` analog of `mapGL_gamma0_mul_T_p_upper_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_delta`.

`╬│тВА ┬╖ M_тИЮ = T_p_lower ┬╖ mapGL ╬╡` where
`╬╡ := gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0 * M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0`
is a product of two ╬УтВБ(N) elements (hence in ╬УтВБ(N)).

Together with the upper-family factorization, this establishes the algebraic
p+1 coset-family identification `╬│тВА ┬╖ ╬▒_i = T_p_lower ┬╖ ╬┤╠Г_i` for every
`i : Option (Fin p)`, where `╬▒_some_b = glMap (T_p_upper p hp b)`,
`╬▒_none = glMap (M_infty N p hp hpN)`, and `╬┤╠Г_i тИИ ╬УтВБ(N)`.  This is the
double-coset bijection underlying DS Theorem 5.5.3.

**Proof**: chain
* `glMap M_тИЮ = glMap T_p_upper(0) ┬╖ mapGL (M_infty_Gamma1_factor 0)` (from
  `glMap_T_p_upper_inv_mul_M_infty_eq_mapGL_Gamma1`, via `mul_inv_cancel_left`),
* `╬│тВА ┬╖ T_p_upper(0) = T_p_lower ┬╖ ╬┤_0` (via the upper-family factorization
  `mapGL_gamma0_mul_T_p_upper_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_delta` at `b = 0`),
* multiplicativity of `mapGL тДЭ` to collect the two ╬УтВБ(N) factors. -/
private theorem mapGL_gamma0_mul_M_infty_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_epsilon
    (N p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hp : 0 < p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N) :
    ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
      (glMap (M_infty N p hp hpN) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
    (glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
      ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        (gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0 *
          M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := by
  have h_M_infty_eq : (glMap (M_infty N p hp hpN) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) =
      (glMap (T_p_upper p hp 0) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
        ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _) (M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0)) := by
    rw [тЖР glMap_T_p_upper_inv_mul_M_infty_eq_mapGL_Gamma1 N p hp hpN 0,
      mul_inv_cancel_left]
  rw [h_M_infty_eq, тЖР mul_assoc,
    mapGL_gamma0_mul_T_p_upper_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_delta N p hp hpN 0,
    mul_assoc, тЖР map_mul]

/-- **T128 `M_тИЮ` branch ╬УтВБ(N)-membership**: the correction factor `╬╡` from
`mapGL_gamma0_mul_M_infty_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_epsilon` lies in ╬УтВБ(N), as a
product of two ╬УтВБ(N) elements (the ╬┤_0 factor + the M_тИЮ factor at b = 0). -/
private theorem gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor_zero_mul_M_infty_Gamma1_factor_zero_mem_Gamma1
    (N p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N) :
    gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0 * M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0 тИИ
      Gamma1 N :=
  mul_mem (gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor_mem_Gamma1 N p hpN 0)
    (M_infty_Gamma1_factor_mem_Gamma1 N p hpN 0)

/-- **T128 p+1 coset family ╬УтВБ(N)-correction**: the Option (Fin p)-indexed
family of ╬УтВБ(N) correction factors `╬┤╠Г_i` satisfying
`╬│тВА ┬╖ ╬▒_i = T_p_lower ┬╖ mapGL (╬┤╠Г_i)`, where
`╬▒_some_b = glMap (T_p_upper p hp b)`, `╬▒_none = glMap (M_infty N p hp hpN)`.

This packages the p+1 DS coset-family identification into a single
`Option (Fin p)`-indexed family, giving the algebraic backbone of the
sum-level double-coset aggregation. -/
private noncomputable def ds_p_plus_one_family_Gamma1_factor
    (N p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N) :
    Option (Fin p) тЖТ SL(2, тДд)
  | none => gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0 * M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0
  | some b => gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN b.val

/-- **T128 p+1 coset family ╬УтВБ(N)-membership**: every member of the
correction family `ds_p_plus_one_family_Gamma1_factor` lies in ╬УтВБ(N). -/
private theorem ds_p_plus_one_family_Gamma1_factor_mem_Gamma1
    (N p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N) (i : Option (Fin p)) :
    ds_p_plus_one_family_Gamma1_factor N p hpN i тИИ Gamma1 N := by
  match i with
  | none =>
    exact gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor_zero_mul_M_infty_Gamma1_factor_zero_mem_Gamma1
      N p hpN
  | some b =>
    exact gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor_mem_Gamma1 N p hpN b.val

/-- **T128 p+1 coset family aggregate factorization**: uniform statement of
`╬│тВА ┬╖ ╬▒_i = T_p_lower ┬╖ mapGL (╬┤╠Г_i)` for every `i : Option (Fin p)` from the
DS coset family `{glMap (T_p_upper p hp b) : b тИИ Fin p} тИк {glMap (M_infty)}`.

This is the **algebraic p+1 coset-family reindex including `M_тИЮ`** тАФ the
minimal double-coset aggregate infrastructure for the `T_p` / `T_p_lower`
bridge across all Option (Fin p) representatives, obtained by combining the
upper-family factorization with the M_тИЮ branch via the `M_infty_Gamma1_factor`
decomposition. -/
private theorem mapGL_gamma0_mul_ds_family_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_factor
    (N p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hp : 0 < p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (i : Option (Fin p)) :
    ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
      (match i with
        | none => (glMap (M_infty N p hp hpN) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
        | some b => (glMap (T_p_upper p hp b.val) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) =
    (glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
      ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        (ds_p_plus_one_family_Gamma1_factor N p hpN i) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) := by
  match i with
  | none =>
    exact mapGL_gamma0_mul_M_infty_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_epsilon N p hp hpN
  | some b =>
    exact mapGL_gamma0_mul_T_p_upper_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_delta N p hp hpN b.val

open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T205-d-SYMM geometric step**: `╬│тВА тАв (╬▒_X тАв D) = T_p_lower тАв (╬│_X тАв D)`
as sets on `тДН`, derived from the matrix identity
`mapGL_gamma0_mul_ds_family_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_factor` by `mul_smul`
associativity.

For each Hecke representative `╬▒_X тИИ {M_тИЮ} тИк {T_p_upper(b)}_{bтИИFin p}` and
the corresponding ╬УтВБ(N)-correction factor `╬│_X = ds_p_plus_one_family_Gamma1_factor X`,
╬│тВА-left-translation of the ╬▒_X-shifted set D equals T_p_lower-left-translation of
the ╬│_X-shifted set D.

**Use in ╧Г_p Q-permutation reduction.** Summing over X yields
`╬│тВА тАв Hecke_FD = T_p_lower тАв (тЛГ_X ╬│_X тАв ╬УтВБ_FD)`, the key geometric identity
underlying the genuine DS Prop 5.5.2(b) ╧Г_p Q-permutation. -/
private theorem gamma0_smul_ds_family_eq_T_p_lower_smul_gamma_X
    (p : тДХ) [NeZero N] (hp : 0 < p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (i : Option (Fin p)) (D : Set тДН) :
    ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд)) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) тАв
      ((match i with
        | none => (glMap (M_infty N p hp hpN) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
        | some b => (glMap (T_p_upper p hp b.val) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) тАв D) =
    (glMap (T_p_lower p hp) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) тАв
      (((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* _)
        (ds_p_plus_one_family_Gamma1_factor N p hpN i) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) тАв D) := by
  rw [тЖР mul_smul, тЖР mul_smul,
    mapGL_gamma0_mul_ds_family_eq_T_p_lower_mul_mapGL_factor N p hp hpN i]

open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T205-d-SYMM iUnion geometric step**: `╬│тВА тАв (тЛГ_X ╬▒_X тАв D) = T_p_lower тАв (тЛГ_X ╬│_X тАв D)`.

The `╬│тВА`-translate of the Hecke FD (= тЛГ_X ╬▒_X тАв ╬УтВБ_FD) equals the `T_p_lower`-translate
of the union of `╬│_X`-shifted ╬УтВБ_FD tiles (where ╬│_X тИИ ╬УтВБ(N) for each X). This is
the key set-level identity for the ╧Г_p Q-permutation: combined with measure-preserving
GL+ action and ╬УтВБ(N)-tile invariance, it converts integrals on `╬│тВА тАв Hecke_FD` to
integrals on `T_p_lower тАв (╬У_p_╬▒-FD)`. -/
private theorem gamma0_smul_Hecke_FD_eq_T_p_lower_smul_iUnion
