open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T024 per-tile match reduction via `peterssonInner_slash_adjoint`.**

Reduces a per-tile Petersson scalar identity of the form expected at
`peterssonInner_M_infty_T_p_upper_tile_sum_matches_per_q_distribute`'s
per-tile hypotheses to **three atomic inputs**:

* `h_tile_eq`: tile AE-equals `╬▓ тАв fd` for some positive-det `╬▓ : GLтВВ(тДЭ)`
  (the **tile shape** тАФ geometric content from the bundle's
  `IsFundamentalDomain`-shifted construction);
* `h_slash_slot1`: matrix algebra on slot-1 (`f тИг ╬▓ = (f тИг ╬▒) тИг ╬│` for the
  desired slot-1 form);
* `h_slash_slot2`: matrix algebra on slot-2
  (`g_const тИг (peterssonAdj ╬▓)тБ╗┬╣ = ╧И_g`).

This is a **strictly narrower** factoring of `h_tile_zero_match` /
`h_tile_succ_match` from the previous reduction theorem: the per-tile
identification is replaced by tile-shape + per-slot matrix-algebra inputs.
The slash-adjoint identity (mathlib-style content) is discharged inline.

**Proof.** The tile-shape AE-equality rewrites the integration domain to
`╬▓ тАв fd`. The standard `g_const = (g_const тИг (peterssonAdj ╬▓)тБ╗┬╣) тИг peterssonAdj ╬▓`
decomposition + `peterssonInner_slash_adjoint` (backward) then converts
`peterssonInner k (╬▓ тАв fd) f g_const` to
`peterssonInner k fd (f тИг ╬▓) (g_const тИг (peterssonAdj ╬▓)тБ╗┬╣)`. The two matrix-
algebra hypotheses discharge the slot identifications.

**Mathematical reference.** DiamondтАУShurman, *A First Course in Modular
Forms*, Prop. 5.5.2(b); Miyake ┬з4.5. -/
private theorem peterssonInner_per_tile_match_via_slash_adjoint
    (╬▓ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) (h╬▓ : 0 < ╬▓.det.val)
    {tile_target : Set UpperHalfPlane}
    (F G : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ)
    (slot1_target slot2_target : UpperHalfPlane тЖТ тДВ)
    (h_tile_eq : tile_target =с╡Р[╬╝_hyp] ╬▓ тАв ModularGroup.fd)
    (h_slash_slot1 : F тИг[k] ╬▓ = slot1_target)
    (h_slash_slot2 : G тИг[k] (peterssonAdj ╬▓)тБ╗┬╣ = slot2_target) :
    peterssonInner k tile_target F G =
      peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd slot1_target slot2_target := by
  have h_tile_inner :
      peterssonInner k tile_target F G =
        peterssonInner k (╬▓ тАв ModularGroup.fd) F G := by
    simp only [peterssonInner]
    exact setIntegral_congr_set h_tile_eq
  rw [h_tile_inner]
  have h_G_decomp : G = (G тИг[k] (peterssonAdj ╬▓)тБ╗┬╣) тИг[k] peterssonAdj ╬▓ := by
    rw [тЖР SlashAction.slash_mul, inv_mul_cancel, SlashAction.slash_one]
  conv_lhs => rw [h_G_decomp]
  rw [тЖР peterssonInner_slash_adjoint ModularGroup.fd ╬▓ h╬▓ F
        (G тИг[k] (peterssonAdj ╬▓)тБ╗┬╣), h_slash_slot1, h_slash_slot2]

open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T024 per-tile match for the M_тИЮ branch.**

Specializes `peterssonInner_per_tile_match_via_slash_adjoint` to the M_тИЮ branch
of the Hecke `T_p` p+1 family by **fixing ╬▓ to `╬│тВАтБ╗┬╣ * q.outтБ╗┬╣`** (the natural
left shift for the bundle's M_тИЮ tile), discharging the slot-1 matrix algebra
inline via `SlashAction.slash_mul`, and isolating the **two genuine atomic
