/-- **T205-d residual: DS Theorem 5.5.3 in symmetric form at petN level.**

The single named analytic residual for `petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form`:
```
  petN(T_p f, g) = petN(тЯиpтЯй f, T_p g)
```
i.e. the petN-level **symmetric** Hecke adjoint identity for the good prime
`T_p` on `╬УтВБ(N)`, the genuine analytic content of DS Thm 5.5.3 / Miyake 4.5.4.

**Why isolated as a single named residual.** The entire scaffold (14-layer
chain via M_тИЮ stockpile, iUnion-form Q-permutation residuals, branch-wise
fd-LHS / tile-shifted forms) reduces to this single petN-level equality via
`petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form_from_petN_symmetric_form`. The per-╬▒
SL-tile balance decomposition is **not** satisfiable individually (each
`(тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣f) тИг glMap M_тИЮ` is only `╬У_p(M_тИЮ)`-invariant, not ╬УтВБ(N)-invariant),
so the correct level for the analytic content is this single aggregate
sum-level identity, not per-tile balances.

**Closure paths (any one suffices).**
1. Direct integral computation using the Hecke double-coset structure at level
   ╬УтВБ(N) (Miyake ┬з4.5; Shimura Thm 3.34). Substitute ╧Д тЖТ ╬▒ ╧Д for each Hecke
   coset rep ╬▒, use M├╢bius-action-invariance of ╬╝_hyp, apply the ╧Г_p
   Q-permutation `Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0 adjointGamma0Rep`.
2. Eigenform basis: T_p is normal under the petN form on each character
   space; symmetric form follows from spectral decomposition (requires
   T207, which itself depends on T205-d тАФ circular).
3. Mathlib's eventual abstract Hecke ring formalization providing adjoint
   identities for unitary representations of the Hecke algebra.

**Maximally compressed reduction landed (2026-05-12 beastmode).** The
sorry is now reducible via the axiom-clean chain
`petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form_from_uniform` to:
* `TpHeckeFamilyMeasureHypotheses` (mechanical measure-theoretic content);
* `TpUniformSigmaPermBlocker M` for `M тИИ {glMap T_p_lower} тИк
  {glMap T_p_lower ┬╖ mapGL ╬│_b}_{b тИИ Finset.range p}` (genuine ╧Г_p
  Q-permutation content, expressed UNIFORMLY across all p+1 Hecke reps).

Equivalent entry points (all axiom-clean wrappers in place):

**Aggregate routes** (MATHEMATICALLY VALID тАФ these capture the full
DS Prop 5.5.2(b) content and ARE satisfiable):
* `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge` (at line ~8350): aggregate sum-level identity
  bridging LHS-distributed and RHS-symmetric sums. Consumed by
  `petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form_of_doubleCosetTileBridge`.  **This is the
  cleanest valid route** тАФ it requires only the AGGREGATE ╧Г_p Q-permutation
  identity at sum level, which IS true (the per-╬▒ decompositions may not
  individually hold; see note below).
* `heckeFD_canonical_SL_tile_balance` (at line ~18768): canonical SL-tile
  balance, consumed by
  `petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form_from_heckeFD_canonical_SL_tile_balance`.

**Per-╬▒ decomposed routes** (may not be individually satisfiable; useful
only for specific (f, g) pairs):
* `h_M_infty_SL_tile_balance` + per-b `h_T_p_upper_SL_tile_balance`
  (via `h_M_infty_SL_tile_balance_iff_uniform` +
  `h_T_p_upper_SL_tile_balance_iff_uniform`);
* `TpHeckeFamilyBlocker` (v1) / `TpHeckeFamilyBlocker_v2` (v2);
* `TpPerQSigmaAlignedBlocker M q` per `(M, q)` (per-q tile-level form);
* `TpPerQSigmaAlignedBlocker_fd M q` per `(M, q)` (per-q **fd-level** form;
  see `petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form_from_per_q_fd`).

**Note on per-╬▒ satisfiability.** As noted in
`heckeT_p_petN_symmetric_residual` doc, the per-╬▒ SL-tile balance is NOT
in general satisfiable for arbitrary (f, g): `(тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣f) тИг glMap M_тИЮ` is
only ╬У_p(M_тИЮ)-invariant, not ╬УтВБ(N)-invariant.  The aggregate
`DSDoubleCosetTileBridge` route bypasses this issue. -/
private theorem petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN) f)
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) := by
  -- Reduce to `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge` via the existing
  -- `petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form_of_doubleCosetTileBridge` consumer.
  -- The remaining content is the genuine analytic ╧Г_p Q-permutation
  -- aggregate identity (DS Prop 5.5.2(b)).
  refine petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form_of_doubleCosetTileBridge p hp hpN f g ?_
  -- `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge p hp hpN f g`: the LHS-distributed sum equals
  -- the RHS-symmetric distributed sum.  Both forms unfold to sums of
  -- `peterssonInner k fd (f тИг ...) (g тИг ...)` terms over `q : SL(2,тДд) тз╕ ╬УтВБ(N)`.
  unfold DSDoubleCosetTileBridge
  -- Apply `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge_of_LHS_dist_eq_RHS_absorbed` to the
  -- ╧Г_p-absorbed RHS form; the remaining content is the
  -- LHS-distributed / RHS-absorbed equality.
  refine DSDoubleCosetTileBridge_of_LHS_dist_eq_RHS_absorbed p hp hpN f g ?_
  -- Reduce via branch decomposition: split into M_тИЮ-branch and upper-b-branch
  -- sum equalities (each a separate sub-residual). The genuine ╧Г_p Q-permutation
  -- aggregate content lives in each branch's sum equality.
  -- Each branch residual: тИС_q LHS-dist@q = тИС_q RHS-╧Г-absorbed@q.
  -- These reduce to a single integral equality on the union-tile
  -- `(T_p_lower ┬╖ ╬│_X) тАв FD_{╬УтВБ(N)}` after applying:
  --  тАв slash-adjoint per q (moves `T_p_lower ┬╖ ╬│_X` from f-slash to domain shift),
  --  тАв SL slash-invariance for `q.outтБ╗┬╣` (absorbs the q-shift into domain),
  --  тАв ╬УтВБ(N)-slash invariance (kills the ╬│_X factor on q-independent slot),
  --  тАв ╧Г-reindex on RHS sum (changes `(╧Гq).outтБ╗┬╣` тЖТ `q'.outтБ╗┬╣` via Equiv.sum_comp),
  --  тАв AE-disjoint sum collapse (turns тИС_q into a single integral over union-tile).
  -- The remaining content is the integral identity (in the M_тИЮ branch case):
  --   тИл_{(T_p_lower┬╖╬│_X)тАвFD} pet f (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯйg тИг T_p_upper(0)) d╬╝
  --     = тИл_{(T_p_lower┬╖╬│_X)тАвFD} pet (тЯиuтБ╗┬╣тЯйf тИг T_p_upper(0)) (тЯиuтЯйg) d╬╝
  -- This is the genuine analytic ╧Г_p Q-permutation content (DS 5.5.2(b)).
  rw [Finset.sum_add_distrib, Finset.sum_add_distrib]
  refine congr_argтВВ (┬╖ + ┬╖) ?_ ?_
  ┬╖ -- M_тИЮ-branch sum residual `SigmaQPermResidual_M_infty p hp hpN f g`.
    -- Reduction infrastructure landed (axiom-clean):
    --  тАв LHS sumтЖТper-q tile-form: `sum_peterssonInner_LHS_M_infty_to_tile_form`
    --  тАв Per-qтЖТunion-tile: `sum_peterssonInner_M_infty_tile_form_collapse`
    -- Remaining: parallel RHS reduction (with ╧Г-reindex via `Equiv.sum_comp`),
    -- then identification of the union-tile integrals (genuine ╧Г_p content).
    show SigmaQPermResidual_M_infty p hp hpN f g
    sorry
  ┬╖ -- upper-b-branch sum residual `SigmaQPermResidual_upper p hp hpN f g`.
    -- Reduction infrastructure landed (axiom-clean):
