/-- **T128 DS-standard aggregate consumer**: DS 5.5.3 in its canonical
`T_p* = тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p` form at petN level: `petN(T_p f, g) = petN(f, тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣(T_p g))`.

Discharged via the clean chain through `petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form` (the
single named DS 5.5.3 symmetric residual). The entire 14-layer scaffold is
bypassed: `petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form_from_petN_symmetric_form`
composes the symmetric form with the existing reverse derivation to produce
the standard form. -/
private lemma petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN f (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) := by
  -- Unfold petN LHS to тИС_q form and apply the per-q union-tile consumer
  -- (distribute + combine + integrability).
  show тИС q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N,
      UpperHalfPlane.peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
        (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) тИг[k] ((q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣))
        (тЗСg тИг[k] ((q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)) = _
  have h_per_q : тИА q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N,
      UpperHalfPlane.peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
        (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) тИг[k] ((q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣))
        (тЗСg тИг[k] ((q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣)) =
      UpperHalfPlane.peterssonInner k
        ((glMap (M_infty N p hp.pos hpN) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) тАв
          (((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ :
              GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) тАв
            (ModularGroup.fd : Set UpperHalfPlane)))
        тЗСf
        ((тЗСg тИг[k] (glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos 0) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) тИг[k]
          ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
            ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд)))) +
      UpperHalfPlane.peterssonInner k
        (тЛГ b тИИ Finset.range p,
          ((glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos b) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
            ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ :
              GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) тАв
            (ModularGroup.fd : Set UpperHalfPlane))
        тЗСf
        ((тЗСg тИг[k] (glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos 0) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) тИг[k]
          ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
            ((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, тДд)))) := fun q => by
    change UpperHalfPlane.peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
      (тЗС(heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) тИг[k]
        ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ :
          GL (Fin 2) тДЭ))
      (тЗСg тИг[k] ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
        (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)) = _
    exact peterssonInner_heckeT_p_LHS_per_q_to_union_tiles p hp hpN
      (q.out : SL(2, тДд)) f g
  -- Discharged via the clean chain through `petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form`:
  -- the entire 14-layer scaffold (M_тИЮ stockpile, iUnion residuals, ╧Г_p reindex
  -- at sum level, branch-wise q-decompositions) is bypassed by composing
  -- `petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form_from_petN_symmetric_form` with the
  -- single named DS 5.5.3 symmetric residual.
  exact petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form_from_petN_symmetric_form p hp hpN f g
    (petN_heckeT_p_symmetric_form p hp hpN f g)

/-- **T128 canonical petN-level adjoint residual**: the DS 5.5.3 adjoint
identity in its canonical form, `petN(T_p f, g) = petN(f, T_p(тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ g))`.

Derived from `petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form` (DS-standard aggregate
consumer) via `heckeT_p_comm_diamondOp` (the T_p/diamond commutation), which
swaps `T_p(тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ g)` and `тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣(T_p g)` on the right-hand slot. -/
private theorem petN_heckeT_p_canonical_adjoint_residual
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN f (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN
        (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ g)) := by
  rw [show (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN
        (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ g) :
        CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) =
      diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) from by
    apply CuspForm.ext; intro ╧Д
    show ((heckeT_p k p hp hpN)
        (diamondOp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣ g.toModularForm')).toFun ╧Д =
      ((diamondOp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣)
        (heckeT_p k p hp hpN g.toModularForm')).toFun ╧Д
    have h := LinearMap.congr_fun
      (heckeT_p_comm_diamondOp k p hp hpN (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣)
      g.toModularForm'
    exact congr_arg (fun m : ModularForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k => m.toFun ╧Д)
      h.symm]
  exact petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form p hp hpN f g

/-- **T090 reusable reduction**: symmetric Hecke adjoint from unsymmetric.

Given the unsymmetric T_p adjoint identity in its canonical DiamondтАУShurman
form `petN(T_p f, g) = petN(f, тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣(T_p g))`, derive the symmetric form
`petN(T_p f, g) = petN(тЯиpтЯй f, T_p g)` by a single application of diamond
unitarity (`diamondOp_petersson_unitary`) followed by the cancellation
`тЯиpтЯй тИШ тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ = id` on the right slot.

This is purely an algebraic adapter at the Petersson level: it does **not**
re-enter the ╬УтВА-reindex / ╬УтВБ-quotient combinatorial machinery, and it has
no measurability or integrability side conditions beyond what
`diamondOp_petersson_unitary` already encapsulates.

**Role.** Reusable theorem-level slice (T090): packages the entire DS 5.5.3
chain so that any closure of the unsymmetric form (e.g. directly proving
`petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form` from the sum-level fundamental-domain
tiling / coset-representative bijection) immediately yields the symmetric
target `petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core` without further analytic work. -/
private theorem petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core_of_unsymm
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k)
    (h_unsymm : petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN f (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g))) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN) f)
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) := by
  set u := ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN
  have h_cancel : diamondOp_cusp k u (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣
      (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) = heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g := by
    show diamondOpCusp k u (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) =
      heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g
    rw [show diamondOpCusp k u (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) =
        ((diamondOpCusp k u).comp (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣))
          (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) from rfl,
      тЖР diamondOpCusp_mul, mul_inv_cancel, diamondOpCusp_one]
    rfl
  have h2 := diamondOp_petersson_unitary u f
    (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g))
  calc petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g
      = petN f (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) := h_unsymm
    _ = petN (diamondOp_cusp k u f)
          (diamondOp_cusp k u
            (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g))) := h2.symm
    _ = petN (diamondOp_cusp k u f) (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) := by
        rw [h_cancel]

/-- **DS Theorem 5.5.3** (symmetric form): `petN(T_p f, g) = petN(тЯиpтЯйf, T_p g)`.

Now a direct one-line consequence of the T090 reusable reduction
`petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core_of_unsymm` applied to the unsymmetric
adjoint identity `petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form`. The previous proof
went through `petN_heckeT_p_canonical_adjoint_residual` and re-ran the
╬УтВА-reindex chain; the new path bypasses those intermediates entirely. -/
private theorem petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN) f)
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) :=
  petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core_of_unsymm p hp hpN f g
    (petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form p hp hpN f g)

/-- **Adjoint form of `T_p`** (DS Theorem 5.5.3):
`petN(T_p f, g) = petN(f, тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g)`. -/
private theorem petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_unsymm
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN f (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) := by
  set u := ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN
  have h1 := petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core p hp hpN f g
  have h_cancel : diamondOp_cusp k u (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣
      (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) = heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g := by
    show diamondOpCusp k u (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) =
      heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g
    rw [show diamondOpCusp k u (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) =
        ((diamondOpCusp k u).comp (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣)) (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) from rfl,
      тЖР diamondOpCusp_mul, mul_inv_cancel, diamondOpCusp_one]
    rfl
  have h2 := diamondOp_petersson_unitary u f
    (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g))
  calc petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g
      = petN (diamondOp_cusp k u f) (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) := h1
    _ = petN (diamondOp_cusp k u f) (diamondOp_cusp k u
          (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g))) := by
        rw [h_cancel]
    _ = petN f (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) := h2

/-- Core double-coset identity for the Hecke adjoint (DS Theorem 5.5.3):
`тЯиT_p f, gтЯй_N = тЯитЯиpтЯйf, T_p gтЯй_N`.

Now a direct consequence of `petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core`. -/
private theorem petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN) f)
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) :=
  petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift_core p hp hpN f g

/-- Derives `heckeT_p_adjoint` from `petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift` via
`diamondOp_petersson_unitary`. -/
private theorem heckeT_p_adjoint_of_diamond_shift
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN f (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) := by
  -- Chain: petN(T_p f, g) = petN(тЯиpтЯйf, T_p g) = petN(f, тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g)
  set u := ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN
  -- Step 1: petN(T_p f, g) = petN(тЯиuтЯйf, T_p g)
  have h1 := petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift p hp hpN f g
  -- Step 2: тЯиuтЯй(тЯиuтЯйтБ╗┬╣ (T_p g)) = T_p g
  have h_cancel : diamondOp_cusp k u (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣
      (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) = heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g := by
    show diamondOpCusp k u (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) =
      heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g
    rw [show diamondOpCusp k u (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) =
        ((diamondOpCusp k u).comp (diamondOpCusp k uтБ╗┬╣)) (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) from rfl,
      тЖР diamondOpCusp_mul, mul_inv_cancel, diamondOpCusp_one]
    rfl
  -- Step 3: petN(тЯиuтЯйf, тЯиuтЯй(тЯиuтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g)) = petN(f, тЯиuтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g)
  have h2 := diamondOp_petersson_unitary u f
    (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g))
  -- Combine:
  --   petN(T_p f, g) = petN(тЯиuтЯйf, T_p g)             [h1]
  --                   = petN(тЯиuтЯйf, тЯиuтЯй(тЯиuтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g)) [h_cancelтБ╗┬╣ on 2nd arg]
  --                   = petN(f, тЯиuтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g)          [h2]
  calc petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g
      = petN (diamondOp_cusp k u f) (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g) := h1
    _ = petN (diamondOp_cusp k u f) (diamondOp_cusp k u
          (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g))) := by
        rw [h_cancel]
    _ = petN f (diamondOp_cusp k uтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) := h2

/-- **DS Theorem 5.5.3**: `T_p* = тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p` w.r.t. the level-N Petersson product
`petN`, i.e. `тЯиT_p f, gтЯй_N = тЯиf, тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p gтЯй_N`.

The proof reduces to `petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift` (the symmetric form
`тЯиT_p f, gтЯй = тЯитЯиpтЯйf, T_p gтЯй`) via `diamondOp_petersson_unitary`:
```
  petN(T_p f, g) = petN(тЯиpтЯйf, T_p g)           [petN_heckeT_p_diamond_shift]
                 = petN(тЯиpтЯйf, тЯиpтЯй(тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g)) [тЯиpтЯйтИШтЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ = id]
                 = petN(f, тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g)          [diamondOp_petersson_unitary]
```
-/
theorem heckeT_p_adjoint
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN f) g =
      petN f (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_p_cusp k p hp hpN g)) :=
  heckeT_p_adjoint_of_diamond_shift p hp hpN f g

/-! ### Helper lemmas for `heckeT_n_adjoint` -/

/-- `T_n` commutes with `тЯиdтЯй` at the CuspForm level: for `(n, N) = 1`,
`T_n(тЯиdтЯй f) = тЯиdтЯй(T_n f)`. Follows from `heckeT_n_comm_diamondOp`. -/
private theorem heckeT_n_cusp_comm_diamondOp (n : тДХ) [NeZero n]
    (hn : Nat.Coprime n N) (d : (ZMod N)╦г)
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    heckeT_n_cusp k n (diamondOp_cusp k d f) =
      diamondOp_cusp k d (heckeT_n_cusp k n f) := by
  apply CuspForm.ext; intro ╧Д
  show ((heckeT_n k n) (diamondOp k d f.toModularForm')).toFun ╧Д =
    ((diamondOp k d) (heckeT_n k n f.toModularForm')).toFun ╧Д
  have h := congr_fun (congr_arg DFunLike.coe (heckeT_n_comm_diamondOp k n hn d))
    f.toModularForm'
  simp only [Module.End.mul_apply] at h
  exact congr_arg (fun m : ModularForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k => m.toFun ╧Д) h.symm

/-- CuspForm-level decomposition: `T_m f = T_{p^v}(T_{m/p^v} f)` for `m > 1`. -/
private theorem heckeT_n_cusp_decomp (m : тДХ) [NeZero m] (hm : 1 < m)
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    let p := m.minFac
    let hp := Nat.minFac_prime (by omega : m тЙа 1)
    let v := m.factorization p
    haveI : NeZero (p ^ v) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos v).ne'тЯй
    haveI : NeZero (m / p ^ v) :=
      тЯи(Nat.div_pos (Nat.le_of_dvd (by omega) (Nat.ordProj_dvd m p))
        (pow_pos hp.pos v)).ne'тЯй
    heckeT_n_cusp k m f =
      heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ v) (heckeT_n_cusp k (m / p ^ v) f) := by
  apply CuspForm.ext; intro z
  exact heckeT_n_cusp_unfold m hm f z

/-- `T_m(T_n f) = T_n(T_m f)` at the CuspForm level. Follows from `heckeT_n_comm`. -/
private theorem heckeT_n_cusp_comm (m n : тДХ) [NeZero m] [NeZero n]
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    heckeT_n_cusp k m (heckeT_n_cusp k n f) =
      heckeT_n_cusp k n (heckeT_n_cusp k m f) := by
  apply CuspForm.ext; intro ╧Д
  show ((heckeT_n k m) ((heckeT_n k n) f.toModularForm')).toFun ╧Д =
    ((heckeT_n k n) ((heckeT_n k m) f.toModularForm')).toFun ╧Д
  have h := congr_fun (congr_arg DFunLike.coe (heckeT_n_comm k m n)) f.toModularForm'
  simp only [Module.End.mul_apply] at h
  exact congr_arg (fun m : ModularForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k => m.toFun ╧Д) h

/-- `тЯиdтВБтЯй(тЯиdтВВтЯй f) = тЯиdтВБ * dтВВтЯй f` at the CuspForm level. -/
private theorem diamondOp_cusp_comp (dтВБ dтВВ : (ZMod N)╦г)
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    diamondOp_cusp k dтВБ (diamondOp_cusp k dтВВ f) =
      diamondOp_cusp k (dтВБ * dтВВ) f := by
  show diamondOpCusp k dтВБ (diamondOpCusp k dтВВ f) = diamondOpCusp k (dтВБ * dтВВ) f
  rw [show diamondOpCusp k dтВБ (diamondOpCusp k dтВВ f) =
    ((diamondOpCusp k dтВБ).comp (diamondOpCusp k dтВВ)) f from rfl,
    тЖР diamondOpCusp_mul]

/-- `тЯи1тЯй f = f` at the CuspForm level. -/
private theorem diamondOp_cusp_one
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    diamondOp_cusp k (1 : (ZMod N)╦г) f = f := by
  show diamondOpCusp k 1 f = f
  have := congr_fun (congr_arg DFunLike.coe (diamondOpCusp_one (N := N) (k := k))) f
  exact CuspForm.ext fun ╧Д => congr_arg (fun m => m ╧Д) this

/-- The coprime-factorization step of the `heckeT_n_adjoint` induction.
Given `m = nтВБ * nтВВ` with the IH for both factors, chains:
```
petN(T_m f, g) = petN(T_{nтВБ}(T_{nтВВ} f), g)       [decomp]
             = petN(T_{nтВВ} f, тЯиnтВБтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_{nтВБ} g)    [IH on nтВБ]
             = petN(f, тЯиnтВВтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_{nтВВ}(тЯиnтВБтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_{nтВБ} g))  [IH on nтВВ]
             = petN(f, тЯиnтВВтЯйтБ╗┬╣ тЯиnтВБтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_{nтВВ}(T_{nтВБ} g))  [T_{nтВВ} comm тЯиnтВБтЯйтБ╗┬╣]
             = petN(f, тЯиmтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_m g)                [unit mult + decomp]
``` -/
private theorem heckeT_n_adjoint_coprime_case (m : тДХ) [NeZero m]
    (hcop : Nat.Coprime m N) (nтВБ nтВВ : тДХ) [NeZero nтВБ] [NeZero nтВВ]
    (hnтВБ_cop : Nat.Coprime nтВБ N) (hnтВВ_cop : Nat.Coprime nтВВ N)
    (hpv_dvd : nтВБ тИг m) (hdiv_eq : nтВВ = m / nтВБ)
    (hDecomp : тИА h : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
        heckeT_n_cusp k m h =
          heckeT_n_cusp k nтВБ (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВВ h))
    (ih_nтВБ : тИА fтВА gтВА : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
        petN (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВБ fтВА) gтВА =
          petN fтВА (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime nтВБ hnтВБ_cop)тБ╗┬╣
            (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВБ gтВА)))
    (ih_nтВВ : тИА fтВА gтВА : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
        petN (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВВ fтВА) gтВА =
          petN fтВА (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime nтВВ hnтВВ_cop)тБ╗┬╣
            (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВВ gтВА)))
    (f' g' : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_n_cusp k m f') g' =
      petN f' (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime m hcop)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_n_cusp k m g')) := by
  -- Step 1: T_m f' = T_{nтВБ}(T_{nтВВ} f')
  rw [hDecomp f']
  -- Step 2: Apply IH on nтВБ
  rw [ih_nтВБ (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВВ f') g']
  -- Step 3: Apply IH on nтВВ
  rw [ih_nтВВ f' (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime nтВБ hnтВБ_cop)тБ╗┬╣
    (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВБ g'))]
  -- Step 4: Commutativity: T_{nтВВ}(тЯиnтВБтЯйтБ╗┬╣ h) = тЯиnтВБтЯйтБ╗┬╣(T_{nтВВ} h)
  rw [heckeT_n_cusp_comm_diamondOp nтВВ hnтВВ_cop
    (ZMod.unitOfCoprime nтВБ hnтВБ_cop)тБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВБ g')]
  -- Step 5: Compose diamonds, commute Hecke operators, match units
  rw [diamondOp_cusp_comp]
  -- Hecke comm + decomp: T_{nтВВ}(T_{nтВБ} g') = T_{nтВБ}(T_{nтВВ} g') = T_m g'
  have h_hecke : heckeT_n_cusp k nтВВ (heckeT_n_cusp k nтВБ g') = heckeT_n_cusp k m g' :=
    (heckeT_n_cusp_comm nтВВ nтВБ g').trans (hDecomp g').symm
  have h_unit : (ZMod.unitOfCoprime nтВВ hnтВВ_cop)тБ╗┬╣ * (ZMod.unitOfCoprime nтВБ hnтВБ_cop)тБ╗┬╣ =
      (ZMod.unitOfCoprime m hcop)тБ╗┬╣ := by
    rw [тЖР mul_inv]; congr 1; ext
    simp only [Units.val_mul, ZMod.coe_unitOfCoprime]; rw [mul_comm]
    exact_mod_cast congr_arg (Nat.cast (R := ZMod N))
      (show (nтВБ : тДХ) * nтВВ = m from by rw [hdiv_eq]; exact Nat.mul_div_cancel' hpv_dvd)
  simp only [h_hecke, h_unit]

/-- CuspForm-level prime-power recursion:
`T_{p^{r+2}} f = T_p(T_{p^{r+1}} f) - p^{k-1} тАв тЯиpтЯй(T_{p^r} f)`.

Lifts `heckeT_ppow_succ_succ` from `Module.End` to `CuspForm`. -/
private theorem heckeT_n_cusp_ppow_recursion (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p)
    (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N) (r : тДХ)
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    haveI : NeZero p := тЯиhp.ne_zeroтЯй
    haveI : NeZero (p ^ (r + 2)) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos _).ne'тЯй
    haveI : NeZero (p ^ (r + 1)) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos _).ne'тЯй
    haveI : NeZero (p ^ r) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos _).ne'тЯй
    heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ (r + 2)) f =
      heckeT_n_cusp k p (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ (r + 1)) f) -
        (тЖСp : тДВ) ^ (k - 1) тАв diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN)
          (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ r) f) := by
  haveI : NeZero p := тЯиhp.ne_zeroтЯй
  haveI : NeZero (p ^ (r + 2)) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos _).ne'тЯй
  haveI : NeZero (p ^ (r + 1)) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos _).ne'тЯй
  haveI : NeZero (p ^ r) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos _).ne'тЯй
  apply CuspForm.ext; intro ╧Д
  -- Work at Module.End level
  show (heckeT_n k (p ^ (r + 2)) f.toModularForm').toFun ╧Д =
    ((heckeT_n k p) ((heckeT_n k (p ^ (r + 1))) f.toModularForm')).toFun ╧Д -
      (тЖСp : тДВ) ^ (k - 1) тАв
        ((diamondOp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hpN))
          ((heckeT_n k (p ^ r)) f.toModularForm')).toFun ╧Д
  rw [heckeT_n_prime_pow k hp (r + 2) (by omega), heckeT_n_prime_pow k hp (r + 1) (by omega),
      heckeT_n_prime_coprime k hp hpN]
  -- Now both sides use heckeT_ppow / heckeT_p / diamondOp
  rw [heckeT_ppow_succ_succ k p hp r]
  -- LHS: (heckeT_p_all * heckeT_ppow (r+1) - c тАв (diamondOp_ext * heckeT_ppow r)) f
  rw [diamondOp_ext_coprime k hpN, heckeT_p_all_coprime k hp hpN]
  simp only [LinearMap.sub_apply, Module.End.mul_apply, LinearMap.smul_apply,
    ModularForm.sub_apply]
  -- Now need to handle the heckeT_ppow on RHS
  conv_rhs =>
    rw [show heckeT_n k (p ^ r) = heckeT_ppow (N := N) k p hp r from by
        rcases r with _ | r
        ┬╖ simp [heckeT_n, heckeT_n_aux, heckeT_ppow]
        ┬╖ exact heckeT_n_prime_pow k hp _ (by omega)]
  rfl

/-- The diamond cancel lemma: `тЯиdтЯй(тЯиdтЯйтБ╗┬╣ f) = f`. -/
private theorem diamondOp_cusp_cancel (d : (ZMod N)╦г)
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    diamondOp_cusp k d (diamondOp_cusp k dтБ╗┬╣ f) = f := by
  show diamondOpCusp k d (diamondOpCusp k dтБ╗┬╣ f) = f
  rw [show diamondOpCusp k d (diamondOpCusp k dтБ╗┬╣ f) =
      ((diamondOpCusp k d).comp (diamondOpCusp k dтБ╗┬╣)) f from rfl,
    тЖР diamondOpCusp_mul, mul_inv_cancel, diamondOpCusp_one]
  rfl

/-- The diamond cancel lemma: `тЯиdтЯйтБ╗┬╣(тЯиdтЯй f) = f`. -/
private theorem diamondOp_cusp_inv_cancel (d : (ZMod N)╦г)
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    diamondOp_cusp k dтБ╗┬╣ (diamondOp_cusp k d f) = f := by
  show diamondOpCusp k dтБ╗┬╣ (diamondOpCusp k d f) = f
  rw [show diamondOpCusp k dтБ╗┬╣ (diamondOpCusp k d f) =
      ((diamondOpCusp k dтБ╗┬╣).comp (diamondOpCusp k d)) f from rfl,
    тЖР diamondOpCusp_mul, inv_mul_cancel, diamondOpCusp_one]
  rfl

/-- `petN(тЯиdтЯй f, g) = petN(f, тЯиdтЯйтБ╗┬╣ g)` тАФ diamond adjoint from diamond unitarity. -/
private theorem petN_diamondOp_adjoint (d : (ZMod N)╦г)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (diamondOp_cusp k d f) g =
      petN f (diamondOp_cusp k dтБ╗┬╣ g) := by
  calc petN (diamondOp_cusp k d f) g
      = petN (diamondOp_cusp k d f) (diamondOp_cusp k d (diamondOp_cusp k dтБ╗┬╣ g)) := by
        rw [diamondOp_cusp_cancel]
    _ = petN f (diamondOp_cusp k dтБ╗┬╣ g) := diamondOp_petersson_unitary d f _

/-- `starRingEnd тДВ ((тЖСp : тДВ) ^ (k - 1)) = (тЖСp : тДВ) ^ (k - 1)` тАФ the scalar is real. -/
private theorem conj_natCast_zpow (p : тДХ) : starRingEnd тДВ ((тЖСp : тДВ) ^ (k - 1)) =
    (тЖСp : тДВ) ^ (k - 1) := by
  have : starRingEnd тДВ (тЖСp : тДВ) = (тЖСp : тДВ) := by
    rw [show (тЖСp : тДВ) = (тЖС(p : тДЭ) : тДВ) from by push_cast; rfl]
    exact Complex.conj_ofReal _
  rw [map_zpowтВА, this]

/-- The prime-power case of the Hecke adjoint: if the IH holds for all
`j < p^v` with `v тЙе 2`, then
`petN(T_{p^v} f, g) = petN(f, тЯиp^vтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_{p^v} g)`. -/
private theorem heckeT_n_adjoint_ppow_case
    (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (v : тДХ) (hv : 2 тЙд v)
    (hcop : Nat.Coprime (p ^ v) N)
    (ih : тИА j : тДХ, j < p ^ v тЖТ (hj_pos : 0 < j) тЖТ (hj : Nat.Coprime j N) тЖТ
      тИА fтВА gтВА : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
        haveI : NeZero j := тЯиhj_pos.ne'тЯй
        petN (heckeT_n_cusp k j fтВА) gтВА =
          petN fтВА (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime j hj)тБ╗┬╣
            (heckeT_n_cusp k j gтВА)))
    (f' g' : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    haveI : NeZero (p ^ v) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos v).ne'тЯй
    petN (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ v) f') g' =
      petN f' (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ v) hcop)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ v) g')) := by
  haveI : NeZero (p ^ v) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos v).ne'тЯй
  -- Write v = r + 2 for some r
  obtain тЯиr, rflтЯй : тИГ r, v = r + 2 := тЯиv - 2, by omegaтЯй
  -- Key: coprimality propagation
  have hp_cop : Nat.Coprime p N := Nat.Coprime.coprime_dvd_left
    (dvd_pow_self p (by omega : r + 2 тЙа 0)) hcop
  haveI : NeZero p := тЯиhp.ne_zeroтЯй
  haveI : NeZero (p ^ (r + 1)) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos _).ne'тЯй
  haveI : NeZero (p ^ r) := тЯи(pow_pos hp.pos _).ne'тЯй
  have hpv1_cop : Nat.Coprime (p ^ (r + 1)) N := Nat.Coprime.pow_left _ hp_cop
  have hpr_cop : Nat.Coprime (p ^ r) N := Nat.Coprime.pow_left _ hp_cop
  -- Size bounds for IH
  have hp_lt : p < p ^ (r + 2) := by
    calc p = p ^ 1 := (pow_one p).symm
      _ < p ^ (r + 2) := Nat.pow_lt_pow_right hp.one_lt (by omega)
  have hpv1_lt : p ^ (r + 1) < p ^ (r + 2) :=
    Nat.pow_lt_pow_right hp.one_lt (by omega)
  have hpr_lt : p ^ r < p ^ (r + 2) :=
    Nat.pow_lt_pow_right hp.one_lt (by omega : r < r + 2)
  -- Abbreviation
  set up := ZMod.unitOfCoprime p hp_cop
  set c := (тЖСp : тДВ) ^ (k - 1)
  -- Step 1: Apply the CuspForm-level recursion to f'
  rw [heckeT_n_cusp_ppow_recursion p hp hp_cop r f']
  -- LHS = petN(T_p(T_{p^{r+1}} f') - c тАв тЯиpтЯй(T_{p^r} f'), g')
  -- Step 2: petN linearity in first argument
  rw [show (heckeT_n_cusp k p (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ (r + 1)) f') -
      c тАв diamondOp_cusp k up (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ r) f') :
      CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) =
    heckeT_n_cusp k p (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ (r + 1)) f') +
      (-(c тАв diamondOp_cusp k up (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ r) f'))) from sub_eq_add_neg _ _]
  rw [petN_add_left, petN_neg_left, petN_conj_smul_left, conj_natCast_zpow]
  -- LHS = petN(T_p(T_{p^{r+1}} f'), g') - c * petN(тЯиpтЯй(T_{p^r} f'), g')
  -- Step 3: IH for p on the first term
  rw [ih p hp_lt hp.pos hp_cop (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ (r + 1)) f') g']
  -- First term = petN(T_{p^{r+1}} f', тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g')
  -- Step 4: IH for p^{r+1} on the first term
  rw [ih (p ^ (r + 1)) hpv1_lt (pow_pos hp.pos _) hpv1_cop f'
    (diamondOp_cusp k upтБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_n_cusp k p g'))]
  -- First term = petN(f', тЯиp^{r+1}тЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_{p^{r+1}} (тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g'))
  -- Step 5: Diamond adjoint for second term
  rw [petN_diamondOp_adjoint up (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ r) f') g']
  -- Second term = c * petN(T_{p^r} f', тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ g')
  -- Step 6: IH for p^r on the second term
  rw [ih (p ^ r) hpr_lt (pow_pos hp.pos _) hpr_cop f'
    (diamondOp_cusp k upтБ╗┬╣ g')]
  -- Now both terms have the form petN(f', ...)
  -- First:  petN(f', тЯиp^{r+1}тЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_{p^{r+1}}(тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_p g'))
  -- Second: c * petN(f', тЯиp^rтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_{p^r}(тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣ g'))
  -- Commute T with тЯиpтЯйтБ╗┬╣
  rw [heckeT_n_cusp_comm_diamondOp (p ^ (r + 1)) hpv1_cop upтБ╗┬╣
      (heckeT_n_cusp k p g')]
  rw [heckeT_n_cusp_comm_diamondOp (p ^ r) hpr_cop upтБ╗┬╣ g']
  -- Compose diamonds
  rw [diamondOp_cusp_comp, diamondOp_cusp_comp]
  -- Hecke commutativity: T_{p^{r+1}}(T_p g') = T_p(T_{p^{r+1}} g')
  rw [heckeT_n_cusp_comm (p ^ (r + 1)) p g']
  -- Reassemble using petN linearity in second argument
  rw [тЖР petN_smul_right c f', тЖР petN_neg_right, тЖР petN_add_right]
  congr 1
  -- Unit identities: тЯиaтЯйтБ╗┬╣ * тЯиbтЯйтБ╗┬╣ = тЯиa*bтЯйтБ╗┬╣
  have h_unit_prod_v : (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 1)) hpv1_cop)тБ╗┬╣ * upтБ╗┬╣ =
      (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 2)) hcop)тБ╗┬╣ := by
    rw [тЖР mul_inv]; congr 1; ext
    simp only [Units.val_mul, ZMod.coe_unitOfCoprime, up]
    push_cast; ring
  have h_unit_prod_vm1 : (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ r) hpr_cop)тБ╗┬╣ * upтБ╗┬╣ =
      (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 1)) hpv1_cop)тБ╗┬╣ := by
    rw [тЖР mul_inv]; congr 1; ext
    simp only [Units.val_mul, ZMod.coe_unitOfCoprime, up]
    push_cast; ring
  rw [h_unit_prod_v, h_unit_prod_vm1]
  -- Apply recursion on g'
  rw [heckeT_n_cusp_ppow_recursion p hp hp_cop r g']
  -- Distribute тЯиdтЯй over subtraction: тЯиdтЯй(a - b) = тЯиdтЯйa - тЯиdтЯйb
  rw [show diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 2)) hcop)тБ╗┬╣
      (heckeT_n_cusp k p (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ (r + 1)) g') -
        c тАв diamondOp_cusp k up (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ r) g')) =
      diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 2)) hcop)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_n_cusp k p (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ (r + 1)) g')) -
      diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 2)) hcop)тБ╗┬╣
        (c тАв diamondOp_cusp k up (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ r) g')) from by
    show diamondOpCusp k _ _ = diamondOpCusp k _ _ - diamondOpCusp k _ _
    rw [тЖР (diamondOpCusp k _).map_sub]]
  -- тЯиdтЯй commutes with scalar: тЯиdтЯй(c тАв h) = c тАв тЯиdтЯй h
  rw [show diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 2)) hcop)тБ╗┬╣
      (c тАв diamondOp_cusp k up (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ r) g')) =
      c тАв diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 2)) hcop)тБ╗┬╣
        (diamondOp_cusp k up (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ r) g')) from by
    show diamondOpCusp k _ _ = c тАв diamondOpCusp k _ _
    rw [тЖР (diamondOpCusp k _).map_smul]]
  -- тЯиp^{r+2}тЯйтБ╗┬╣ тЯиpтЯй = тЯиp^{r+1}тЯйтБ╗┬╣
  rw [diamondOp_cusp_comp]
  have h_unit_cancel : (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 2)) hcop)тБ╗┬╣ * up =
      (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 1)) hpv1_cop)тБ╗┬╣ := by
    have := h_unit_prod_v
    calc (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 2)) hcop)тБ╗┬╣ * up
        = (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 1)) hpv1_cop)тБ╗┬╣ * upтБ╗┬╣ * up := by
          rw [this]
      _ = (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 1)) hpv1_cop)тБ╗┬╣ * (upтБ╗┬╣ * up) := by
          rw [mul_assoc]
      _ = (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ (r + 1)) hpv1_cop)тБ╗┬╣ := by
          rw [inv_mul_cancel, mul_one]
  rw [h_unit_cancel]
  -- Now LHS = тЯиp^{r+2}тЯйтБ╗┬╣(T_p(T_{p^{r+1}} g')) + -(c тАв тЯиp^{r+1}тЯйтБ╗┬╣(T_{p^r} g'))
  -- RHS = тЯиp^{r+2}тЯйтБ╗┬╣(T_p(T_{p^{r+1}} g')) - c тАв тЯиp^{r+1}тЯйтБ╗┬╣(T_{p^r} g')
  -- These are equal: a + (-b) = a - b
  abel

/-! ### Normality of Hecke operators -/

/-- The Hecke adjoint for general T_n: `T_n* = тЯиnтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_n` on `S_k(╬УтВБ(N))`,
w.r.t. the level-N Petersson inner product `petN`.

This generalises `heckeT_p_adjoint` from primes to all `n` with `(n,N) = 1`.

## Proof strategy

Uses strong induction on `n`, decomposing `n = p^v * (n/p^v)` via `minFac`.
- **Base case** `n = 1`: Both sides equal `petN f g`.
- **Prime case** `n = p` (i.e. `p^v = n` and `v = 1`): Reduces to `heckeT_p_adjoint`.
- **Composite case** `n > 1`: Decompose `n = p^v * (n/p^v)` via `minFac`. When `p^v < n`
  (i.e. n is not a prime power), both factors are strictly smaller and we apply IH to
  each. When `p^v = n` and `v = 1`, n is prime. When `p^v = n` and `v тЙе 2`, we use
  that `p < n` and `p^{v-1} < n` are both strictly smaller.

Reference: [DS] Theorem 5.5.3, [Miy] Theorem 4.5.4. -/
theorem heckeT_n_adjoint
    (n : тДХ) [NeZero n] (hn : Nat.Coprime n N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (heckeT_n_cusp k n f) g =
      petN f (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣
        (heckeT_n_cusp k n g)) := by
  -- Strong induction: strengthen to quantify over all m, f', g'
  suffices key : тИА m : тДХ, (hm : 0 < m) тЖТ (hcop : Nat.Coprime m N) тЖТ
      тИА f' g' : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
        haveI : NeZero m := тЯиhm.ne'тЯй
        petN (heckeT_n_cusp k m f') g' =
          petN f' (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime m hcop)тБ╗┬╣
            (heckeT_n_cusp k m g')) from
    key n (NeZero.pos n) hn f g
  intro m
  induction m using Nat.strong_induction_on with
  | _ m ih =>
    intro hm hcop f' g'
    haveI instm : NeZero m := тЯиhm.ne'тЯй
    by_cases hle : m тЙд 1
    ┬╖ -- m = 1: T_1 = id, тЯи1тЯй = id, both sides equal petN f' g'
      have hm1 : m = 1 := by omega
      subst hm1
      have hT1f : heckeT_n_cusp (N := N) k 1 f' = f' := CuspForm.ext fun ╧Д => by
        show (heckeT_n k 1 f'.toModularForm').toFun ╧Д = f' ╧Д; rw [heckeT_n_one]; rfl
      have hT1g : heckeT_n_cusp (N := N) k 1 g' = g' := CuspForm.ext fun ╧Д => by
        show (heckeT_n k 1 g'.toModularForm').toFun ╧Д = g' ╧Д; rw [heckeT_n_one]; rfl
      have hunit : ZMod.unitOfCoprime 1 hcop = 1 := by
        ext; simp [ZMod.coe_unitOfCoprime]
      rw [hT1f, hT1g, hunit, inv_one, diamondOp_cusp_one]
    ┬╖ -- m > 1: decompose m = p^v * (m/p^v) via minFac
      push_neg at hle
      set p := m.minFac with hp_def
      have hpp : p.Prime := Nat.minFac_prime (by omega : m тЙа 1)
      set v := m.factorization p with hv_def
      have hv_pos : 0 < v := hpp.factorization_pos_of_dvd (by omega) (Nat.minFac_dvd m)
      have hpv_pos : 0 < p ^ v := pow_pos hpp.pos v
      have hdiv_pos : 0 < m / p ^ v :=
        Nat.div_pos (Nat.le_of_dvd (by omega) (Nat.ordProj_dvd m p)) hpv_pos
      have hdiv_lt : m / p ^ v < m := heckeT_n_unfold_lt m hle
      haveI : NeZero (p ^ v) := тЯиhpv_pos.ne'тЯй
      haveI : NeZero (m / p ^ v) := тЯиhdiv_pos.ne'тЯй
      have hpv_cop : Nat.Coprime (p ^ v) N := Nat.Coprime.pow_left v
        (Nat.Coprime.coprime_dvd_left (Nat.minFac_dvd m) hcop)
      have hdiv_cop : Nat.Coprime (m / p ^ v) N :=
        Nat.Coprime.coprime_dvd_left (Nat.div_dvd_of_dvd (Nat.ordProj_dvd m p)) hcop
      -- CuspForm decomposition: T_m f = T_{p^v}(T_{m/p^v} f)
      have hDecomp : тИА h : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
          heckeT_n_cusp k m h =
            heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ v) (heckeT_n_cusp k (m / p ^ v) h) :=
        fun h => heckeT_n_cusp_decomp m hle h
      -- IH on m/p^v (always < m for m > 1)
      have ih_div : тИА fтВА gтВА : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
          petN (heckeT_n_cusp k (m / p ^ v) fтВА) gтВА =
            petN fтВА (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (m / p ^ v) hdiv_cop)тБ╗┬╣
              (heckeT_n_cusp k (m / p ^ v) gтВА)) :=
        fun fтВА gтВА => ih _ hdiv_lt hdiv_pos hdiv_cop fтВА gтВА
      by_cases hpv_lt : p ^ v < m
      ┬╖ -- Case 1: p^v < m (not a prime power), so both p^v and m/p^v are < m
        -- IH on p^v
        have ih_pv : тИА fтВА gтВА : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
            petN (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ v) fтВА) gтВА =
              petN fтВА (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ v) hpv_cop)тБ╗┬╣
                (heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ v) gтВА)) :=
          fun fтВА gтВА => ih _ hpv_lt hpv_pos hpv_cop fтВА gтВА
        exact heckeT_n_adjoint_coprime_case m hcop (p ^ v) (m / p ^ v)
          hpv_cop hdiv_cop (Nat.ordProj_dvd m p) rfl hDecomp ih_pv ih_div f' g'
      ┬╖ -- Case 2: p^v = m (prime power)
        have hpv_eq : p ^ v = m := le_antisymm
          (Nat.le_of_dvd (by omega) (Nat.ordProj_dvd m p)) (not_lt.mp hpv_lt)
        by_cases hv1 : v = 1
        ┬╖ -- v = 1: m = p is prime, reduce to heckeT_p_adjoint
          have hp_m : Nat.Prime m := by rw [тЖР hpv_eq, hv1, pow_one]; exact hpp
          have hTn_eq : тИА h : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
              heckeT_n_cusp k m h = heckeT_p_cusp k m hp_m hcop h :=
            fun h => CuspForm.ext fun ╧Д => by
              show (heckeT_n k m h.toModularForm').toFun ╧Д =
                (heckeT_p k m hp_m hcop h.toModularForm').toFun ╧Д
              rw [heckeT_n_prime_coprime k hp_m hcop]
          rw [hTn_eq f', hTn_eq g']
          exact heckeT_p_adjoint m hp_m hcop f' g'
        ┬╖ -- v тЙе 2: m = p^v, prime power. Use heckeT_n_adjoint_ppow_case.
          have hv2 : 2 тЙд v := by omega
          -- Convert T_m / тЯиmтЯй to T_{p^v} / тЯиp^vтЯй via CuspForm.ext
          have hTn_pv : тИА h : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k,
              heckeT_n_cusp k m h = heckeT_n_cusp k (p ^ v) h := fun h =>
            CuspForm.ext fun ╧Д => by
              show (heckeT_n k m h.toModularForm').toFun ╧Д =
                (heckeT_n k (p ^ v) h.toModularForm').toFun ╧Д
              simp only [heckeT_n, hpv_eq]
          have h_unit_eq : (ZMod.unitOfCoprime m hcop)тБ╗┬╣ =
              (ZMod.unitOfCoprime (p ^ v) hpv_cop)тБ╗┬╣ := by
            congr 1; ext; simp [ZMod.coe_unitOfCoprime, hpv_eq]
          rw [hTn_pv f', hTn_pv g', h_unit_eq]
          -- Now ih has m but the helper needs p^v; adapt via hpv_eq
          exact heckeT_n_adjoint_ppow_case p hpp v hv2 hpv_cop
            (fun j hj hj_pos hj_cop fтВА gтВА => by
              haveI : NeZero j := тЯиhj_pos.ne'тЯй
              exact ih j (hpv_eq тЦ╕ hj) hj_pos hj_cop fтВА gтВА) f' g'

/-- T_n is normal: `T_n T_n* = T_n* T_n` for `(n,N) = 1`.

Since `T_n* = тЯиnтЯйтБ╗┬╣ T_n` and `T_n` commutes with `тЯиnтЯй` (proved by
`heckeT_n_comm_diamondOp`), normality reduces to function-level commutativity.

Reference: [DS] Theorem 5.5.4, [Miy] Theorem 4.5.5. -/
theorem heckeT_n_normal
    (n : тДХ) [NeZero n] (hn : Nat.Coprime n N)
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    heckeT_n_cusp k n (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣
      (heckeT_n_cusp k n f)) =
    diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣
      (heckeT_n_cusp k n (heckeT_n_cusp k n f)) := by
  have hToModT : тИА (h : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k),
      (heckeT_n_cusp k n h).toModularForm' = heckeT_n k n h.toModularForm' := by
    intro h; apply DFunLike.ext; intro ╧Д; rfl
  have hToModD : тИА (h : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k),
      (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣ h).toModularForm' =
        diamondOp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣ h.toModularForm' := by
    intro h; apply DFunLike.ext; intro ╧Д; rfl
  apply DFunLike.ext
  intro ╧Д
  show ((heckeT_n k n) (diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣
    (heckeT_n_cusp k n f)).toModularForm').toFun ╧Д =
      ((diamondOp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣)
        (heckeT_n_cusp k n (heckeT_n_cusp k n f)).toModularForm').toFun ╧Д
  rw [hToModD, hToModT, hToModT, hToModT]
  have h := congr_fun (congr_arg DFunLike.coe
    (heckeT_n_comm_diamondOp k n hn (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣).symm)
    (heckeT_n k n f.toModularForm')
  simp only [Module.End.mul_apply] at h
  exact congr_arg (fun m : ModularForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k => m.toFun ╧Д) h

/-! ### Simultaneous eigenform basis -/

/-- A cusp form is a common eigenfunction of all `T_n` (cusp form version). -/
abbrev IsCommonEigenfunctionCusp (k : тДд)
    (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) : Prop :=
  тИА n : тДХ+, Nat.Coprime n.val N тЖТ
    haveI : NeZero n.val := тЯиn.pos.ne'тЯй
    тИГ a : тДВ, heckeT_n_cusp k n.val f = a тАв f

/-- `heckeT_n_cusp` preserves the cusp-form character space `S_k(╬УтВБ(N), ╧З)`.
Follows from `heckeT_n_preserves_charSpace` (the `ModularForm` version) via
the cusp-form coercion. -/
lemma heckeT_n_cusp_preserves_cuspFormCharSpace
    (k : тДд) (n : тДХ) [NeZero n] (hn : Nat.Coprime n N) (╧З : (ZMod N)╦г тЖТ* тДВ╦г)
    {f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k} (hf : f тИИ cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З) :
    heckeT_n_cusp k n f тИИ cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З := by
  rw [mem_cuspFormCharSpace_iff] at hf тКв
  intro d
  show diamondOpCusp k d (heckeT_n_cusp k n f) = (тЖС(╧З d) : тДВ) тАв heckeT_n_cusp k n f
  have h_comm : diamondOpCusp k d (heckeT_n_cusp k n f) =
      heckeT_n_cusp k n (diamondOpCusp k d f) := by
    ext z
    show ((diamondOp k d) (heckeT_n k n f.toModularForm')).toFun z =
      ((heckeT_n k n) (diamondOp k d f.toModularForm')).toFun z
    have h := DFunLike.congr_fun (heckeT_n_comm_diamondOp k n hn d) f.toModularForm'
    simp only [Module.End.mul_apply] at h
    exact congr_arg (fun m : ModularForm _ _ => m.toFun z) h
  rw [h_comm]
  show heckeT_n_cusp k n (diamondOpCusp k d f) = тЖС(╧З d) тАв heckeT_n_cusp k n f
  have hfd : diamondOpCusp k d f = (тЖС(╧З d) : тДВ) тАв f := hf d
  rw [hfd]
  ext z
  show (heckeT_n k n ((тЖС(╧З d) : тДВ) тАв f).toModularForm').toFun z =
    (тЖС(╧З d) : тДВ) тАв (heckeT_n k n f.toModularForm').toFun z
  rw [show ((тЖС(╧З d) : тДВ) тАв f).toModularForm' = (тЖС(╧З d) : тДВ) тАв f.toModularForm' from rfl, map_smul]
  rfl

/-- `T_n` restricted to `cuspFormCharSpace` as a linear endomorphism. -/
noncomputable def heckeT_n_cusp_charRestrict
    (k : тДд) (n : тДХ) [NeZero n] (hn : Nat.Coprime n N) (╧З : (ZMod N)╦г тЖТ* тДВ╦г) :
    Module.End тДВ (cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З) where
  toFun := fun тЯиf, hfтЯй =>
    тЯиheckeT_n_cusp k n f, heckeT_n_cusp_preserves_cuspFormCharSpace k n hn ╧З hfтЯй
  map_add' := fun тЯиfтВБ, _тЯй тЯиfтВВ, _тЯй => by
    ext z; show (heckeT_n k n (fтВБ + fтВВ).toModularForm').toFun z =
      ((heckeT_n k n fтВБ.toModularForm').toFun z + (heckeT_n k n fтВВ.toModularForm').toFun z)
    rw [show (fтВБ + fтВВ).toModularForm' = fтВБ.toModularForm' + fтВВ.toModularForm' from rfl, map_add]
    rfl
  map_smul' := fun c тЯиf, _тЯй => by
    ext z; show (heckeT_n k n (c тАв f).toModularForm').toFun z =
      c тАв (heckeT_n k n f.toModularForm').toFun z
    rw [show (c тАв f).toModularForm' = c тАв f.toModularForm' from rfl, map_smul]
    rfl

/-- Additivity in the first argument of `petN`. Derived from `petN_add_right` + Hermitian symmetry. -/
private theorem petN_add_left'
    (fтВБ fтВВ g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (fтВБ + fтВВ) g = petN fтВБ g + petN fтВВ g := by
  have h := petN_add_right g fтВБ fтВВ
  have e := congr_arg (starRingEnd тДВ) h
  rw [petN_conj_symm, map_add, petN_conj_symm, petN_conj_symm] at e
  exact e

/-- Conjugate-scalar in the first argument of `petN`. -/
private theorem petN_conj_smul_left'
    (c : тДВ) (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    petN (c тАв f) g = starRingEnd тДВ c * petN f g := by
  simp only [petN, Finset.mul_sum]
  congr 1; ext q
  have hcoe : тЗС(c тАв f) = c тАв тЗСf := rfl
  have h1 : тЗС(c тАв f) тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ = c тАв (тЗСf тИг[k] (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣) := by
    rw [hcoe]
    exact ModularForm.SL_smul_slash k _ тЗСf c
  rw [h1]
  exact UpperHalfPlane.peterssonInner_conj_smul_left k ModularGroup.fd c _ _

/-- `petN f f` has non-negative real part. Each summand is a non-negative real
(by `petN_summand_nonneg`), so the sum is too. -/
lemma petN_self_re_nonneg (f : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) :
    0 тЙд (petN f f).re := by
  simp only [petN, Complex.re_sum]
  apply Finset.sum_nonneg
  intro q _
  obtain тЯиr, hr_nonneg, hr_eqтЯй := petN_summand_nonneg f q
  rw [hr_eq, Complex.ofReal_re]
  exact hr_nonneg

/-- An `InnerProductSpace.Core` instance on `CuspForm` from `petN`.

This provides the algebraic inner product structure needed for the spectral theorem.
The inner product is `тЯкf, gтЯл := petN f g` (conjugate-linear in first, linear in second). -/
noncomputable def petN_innerProductCore :
    @InnerProductSpace.Core тДВ (CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k) _ _ _ where
  inner f g := petN f g
  conj_inner_symm f g := by
    show starRingEnd тДВ (petN g f) = petN f g
    exact petN_conj_symm f g
  re_inner_nonneg f := petN_self_re_nonneg f
  add_left f g h := petN_add_left' f g h
  smul_left f g c := petN_conj_smul_left' c f g
  definite f hf := petN_definite f hf

/-- On `cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З`, `тЯиnтЯйтБ╗┬╣` acts as the scalar `╧З(n)тБ╗┬╣`.
Hence `T_n* = ╧З(n)тБ╗┬╣ ┬╖ T_n` on this space (from `heckeT_n_adjoint`). -/
private lemma heckeT_n_adjoint_on_charSpace
    (╧З : (ZMod N)╦г тЖТ* тДВ╦г)
    (n : тДХ) [NeZero n] (hn : Nat.Coprime n N)
    {f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k}
    (hf : f тИИ cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З) (hg : g тИИ cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З) :
    petN (heckeT_n_cusp k n f) g =
      (тЖС(╧З (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn))тБ╗┬╣ : тДВ) * petN f (heckeT_n_cusp k n g) := by
  rw [heckeT_n_adjoint n hn f g]
  -- petN f (тЯиnтЯйтБ╗┬╣ (T_n g)). On charSpace, тЯиnтЯйтБ╗┬╣ (T_n g) = ╧З(n)тБ╗┬╣ тАв T_n g.
  have hTg : heckeT_n_cusp k n g тИИ cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З :=
    heckeT_n_cusp_preserves_cuspFormCharSpace k n hn ╧З hg
  have h_diamond : diamondOp_cusp k (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣ (heckeT_n_cusp k n g) =
      (тЖС(╧З (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣) : тДВ) тАв heckeT_n_cusp k n g := by
    exact ((mem_cuspFormCharSpace_iff k ╧З _).mp hTg) (ZMod.unitOfCoprime n hn)тБ╗┬╣
  rw [h_diamond]
  -- petN f (c тАв h) = c * petN f h (linear in second arg)
  simp only [map_inv, Units.val_inv_eq_inv_val]
  exact petN_smul_right _ f (heckeT_n_cusp k n g)

open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T024 public Hecke `T_p` adjoint on character space (sum-chain route).**

Public charSpace-level statement of the DS 5.5.3 adjoint relation
`T_p^* = ╧З(p)тБ╗┬╣ ┬╖ T_p` for `f, g тИИ cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З`, derived via the
**sum-level absorbed-RHS chain** `petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form_via_sum_chain`
(no per-q false hypotheses, no closed-branch refactor).

The genuine analytic content of DS 5.5.2(b) is exposed as the explicit named
hypothesis `h_LHS_dist_eq_RHS_absorbed`: the sum-level matrix equality between
the LHS-diamond-distributed form and the absorbed-RHS form (the slot-1 тЖФ
slot-2 Hecke-factorization swap via slash-adjoint plus ╧Г-reindex through
`Gamma1QuotEquivOfGamma0`).

This is the **smallest reusable public theorem** stating Hecke `T_p`
adjointness on the character-space/Petersson form level via the SMO-critical
sum-chain route. Downstream `newform_unique` / simultaneous eigenspace
machinery can wire to this theorem once `h_LHS_dist_eq_RHS_absorbed` is
discharged (e.g., by a worker handling the per-q absorption symmetry of
DS 5.5.2(b) at the sum level).

**Mathematical reference.**  DiamondтАУShurman, *A First Course in Modular
Forms*, Prop. 5.5.2(b) and Thm. 5.5.3; Miyake ┬з4.5. -/
theorem petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_on_charSpace_via_sum_chain
    (╧З : (ZMod N)╦г тЖТ* тДВ╦г) (p : тДХ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    {f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL тДЭ)) k}
    (hf : f тИИ cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З) (hg : g тИИ cuspFormCharSpace k ╧З)
    (h_LHS_dist_eq_RHS_absorbed :
      (тИС q : SL(2, тДд) тз╕ Gamma1 N,
        (peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
            (тЗСf тИг[k]
              ((glMap (T_p_lower p hp.pos) : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ) *
                ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
                  (gamma0_T_p_upper_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0 *
                    M_infty_Gamma1_factor N p hpN 0)) *
                ((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
                  (q.out : SL(2, тДд))тБ╗┬╣ : GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)))
            (тЗСg тИг[k]
              (((mapGL тДЭ : SL(2, тДд) тЖТ* GL (Fin 2) тДЭ)
